{"title_page": "Zee News", "text_new": "{{Use Indian English|date=May 2015}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2015}}\n{{See also|Zee TV}}\n{{Infobox TV channel\n| launch         = {{Launch date and age|df=y|1999|08|27}}\n| logofile        =Zee News.png\n| logoalt          = \n| owner          = [[Essel Group]]\n| headquarters   =[[Noida]], [[Uttar Pradesh]], [[India]]\n| country        = [[India]]\n| language       = [[Hindi]]\n| picture format = [[1080i]] [[HDTV]]<br />{{small|(downscaled to [[4:3]] [[576i]] for the [[SDTV]] feed)}}\n| broadcast area = International\n| share             =  \n| share as of       = \n| share source      =   \n| sister names = [[Zee TV]]\n| terr serv 1      = [[Oqaab]]<br/>(Afghanistan)\n| terr chan 1      = Channel 45\n| sat serv 1 = [[Airtel Digital TV]]\n| sat chan 1 = Channel 311\n| sat serv 2 = [[Dish TV]]\n| sat chan 2 = Channel 651\n| sat serv 3 = [[Reliance Digital TV]]\n| sat chan 3 = Channel 408\n| sat serv 4 = [[Tata Sky]]\n| sat chan 4 =  Channel 511\n| sat serv 5 = [[Videocon D2H]]\n| sat chan 5 = Channel 302\n| cable serv 1 = [[Siti Cable]]\n| cable chan 1 = Channel 303\n| cable serv 2 = [[Cable TV Hong Kong]]\n| cable chan 2 = Channel 852\n| adsl serv 1 = [[Now TV (China)|now TV]]<br/>(Hong Kong)\n| adsl chan 1 = Channel 785\n| adsl serv 2 = [[Dish Network]]<br/>(United States)\n| adsl chan 2 = Channel 708 (SD)\n| online serv 1    = Live Stream (International)\n| online chan 1    = [http://zeenews.india.com/live-tv live Web stream at Zee News]\n| name = Zee News\n| website = {{URL|https://zeenews.india.com/}}\n| logocaption = \n| logosize =190px \n}}\n\n'''Zee News''' is a [[Hindi language|Hindi-language]] news channel owned by the [[Essel Group]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.esselgroup.com/zee-media-corporation-limited.html|title=Our Companies: Zee Media Corporation Limited|last=|first=|date=|website=esselgroup.com|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-02-25}}</ref> It is associated with several other sister news channels which provide coverage in Hindi, English and several regional languages of India. Zee News was launched on 27 August 1999 as Zee Sports Ltd. The company was [[Certificate of incorporation|reincorporated]] on 27 May 2004 as Zee News Ltd.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://www.business-standard.com/company/zee-media-27705/information/company-history|title=Zee Media Corporation Ltd.|date=|work=[[Business Standard]]|access-date=2020-02-25|url-status=live}}</ref> In 2013, Zee News Ltd changed its name to Zee Media Corporation Limited.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/zee-media-corporation-ltd/infocompanyhistory/companyid-18879.cms|title=Zee Media Corporation History {{!}} Zee Media Corporation Information|last=|first=|date=|website=[[The Economic Times]]|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-02-25}}</ref> The Zee News channel is the flagship channel of the company.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ndtv.com/business/stock/zee-media-corporation-ltd_zeenews/reports-directors-report|title=Director Reports, Company Results of Zee Media Corp|last=|first=|date=|website=[[NDTV Profit]]|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-02-25}}</ref>\n\nThe chairman of the group is [[Subhash Chandra]], who is a [[Bharatiya Janata Party]]-backed member of the [[Rajya Sabha]].<ref>{{Cite news|last=Mohan|first=Archis|url=https://www.business-standard.com/article/politics/subhash-chandra-bets-on-bjp-support-for-rajya-sabha-entry-116053101457_1.html|title=Subhash Chandra bets on BJP support for Rajya Sabha entry|date=2016-06-01|work=Business Standard India|access-date=2020-02-24}}</ref> [[Sudhir Chaudhary (journalist)|Sudhir Chaudhary]] is the editor-in-chief of Zee News and the anchor of the prime time show on the channel.<ref name=\"exch1\">{{cite web|url=http://www.exchange4media.mobi/tv/sudhir-chaudhary-now-also-editor-in-chief-of-zee-business_68276.html|title=Sudhir Chaudhary now also editor in Chief of zee business|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://archive.today/20170715163422/http://www.exchange4media.mobi/tv/sudhir-chaudhary-now-also-editor-in-chief-of-zee-business_68276.html|archive-date=15 July 2017|access-date=15 July 2017|df=}}</ref> The channel has been involved in several controversies and has broadcast fabricated news stories on multiple occasions.<ref name=\"fake\">List of sources:\n\n* {{Cite web|url=https://www.nationalheraldindia.com/book-extract/book-extract-republic-tv-age-of-fake-news-and-promoters-in-indian-tv-newsrooms|title=Book extract: Republic TV, age of fake news and promoters in Indian TV newsrooms|last=Bhushan|first=Sandeep|date=2019-06-29|website=[[National Herald (India)|National Herald]]|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-02-25}}\n* {{Cite web|url=https://www.thehindubusinessline.com/blink/read/the-troubling-association-of-zee-and-jlf/article30693362.ece|title=The festival and its funder|last=Jha|first=Aditya Mani|date=2020-01-31|website=[[Business Line]]|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-02-25}}\n* {{Cite web|url=https://www.altnews.in/zee-news-broadcasts-old-unrelated-satellite-visuals-as-destroyed-jem-camp-in-balakot/|title=Zee News broadcasts old, unrelated satellite visuals as destroyed JEM camp in Balakot|last=Patel|first=Jignesh|date=2019-03-08|website=[[Alt News]]|language=en-GB|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-02-25}}\n* {{Cite web|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/india/india-news-india/zee-news-producer-quits-video-we-shot-had-no-pakistan-zindabad-slogan/|title=Zee News producer quits: Video we shot had no Pakistan Zindabad slogan|last=Hafeez|first=Sarah|date=2018-02-22|website=[[The Indian Express]]|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-02-25}}\n* {{Cite web|url=https://www.outlookindia.com/magazine/story/india-news-are-newsrooms-run-by-political-masters-why-are-editors-compromising-on-truth-telling/302846|title=Are Newsrooms Run By Political Masters? Why Are Editors Compromising On Truth Telling?|last=Yadav|first=Puneet|date=2020-02-21|website=[[Outlook (Indian magazine)|Outlook]]|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-02-25}}\n* {{Cite web|url=https://theprint.in/hoaxposed/zee-news-tweets-doctored-video-of-navjot-sidhus-rajasthan-rally/158011/|title=Zee News tweets doctored video of Navjot Sidhu\u2019s Rajasthan rally|last=Rampal|first=Nikhil|date=2018-12-03|website=[[ThePrint]]|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-02-25}}\n* {{Cite web|url=http://www.catchnews.com/politics-news/saffron-journalism-zee-news-and-art-of-manufacturing-anti-nationals-1457687402.html|title=Saffron journalism: Zee News & art of manufacturing anti-nationals|last=Menon|first=Aditya|date=10 February 2017|website=catchnews.com|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-02-25}}\n* {{Cite web|url=https://www.dailyo.in/politics/zee-news-subhash-chandra-sudhir-chaudhary-narendra-modi-bhakt-sangh-jnu-bjp-muslims-pakistan-anupam-kher/story/1/9474.html|title=Subhash Chandra failed to convince Zee is not Modi's mouthpiece|last=Khan|first=Saif Ahmed|date=2016-03-10|website=[[India Today|DailyO]]|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-02-25}}</ref> The channel is subjected to an ongoing criminal defamation case against legislator [[Mahua Moitra]] as of March 2020.<ref name=\":3\" />\n\n== Outlets ==\n\n=== Television ===\nThe Zee Media Corporation Limited (ZMCL) operates a number of other channels, some in regional languages with the stated intent of providing a pan-Indian reach.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://in.reuters.com/finance/stocks/company-profile/ZEEN.BO|title=Profile: Zee Media Corporation Ltd (ZEEN.BO)|last=|first=|date=|website=[[Reuters]]|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-02-25}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.moneycontrol.com/news/business/companies/zee-media-to-foray-into-english-news-broadcasting-1512583.html|title=Zee Media to foray into English news broadcasting|last=|first=|date=17 August 2015|website=[[Moneycontrol]]|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-02-25}}</ref><ref name=\":0\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.zeemedia.in/channeloverview.html|title=ZMCL Channels Overview|last=|first=|date=|website=www.zeemedia.in|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-02-25}}</ref>\n\n* '''World is One News (WION):''' [[English language]] news channel.\n* '''Zee Business:''' Hindi language business news channel.\n*'''Zee Hindustan:''' 24/7 national Hindi language news channel. It was relaunched in 2017 as an anchor-less news channel.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.exchange4media.com/media-tv-news/zee-hindustan-re-launched-as-anchor-less-channel-93472.html|title=Zee Hindustan re-launched as anchor-less channel - Exchange4media|last=|first=|date=|website=exchange4media.com|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-02-25}}</ref> It was formerly branded as Zee Sangam and India 24x7.<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=https://bestmediainfo.com/2017/05/india-24x7-is-now-zee-hindustan/|title=India 24x7 is now Zee Hindustan|last=|first=|last2=|date=23 May 2017|website=Best Media Info|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-02-25|last3=}}</ref>\n* '''[[Zee 24 Taas]]:''' 24/7 [[Marathi language]] regional news channel.\n*'''Zee 24 Kalak:''' 24/7 [[Gujarati language]] regional news channel. It was inaugurated on 20 August 2017 by [[Vijay Rupani]], the [[Chief minister (India)|Chief Minister]] of Gujarat.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dnaindia.com/india/report-gujarat-cm-deputy-cm-launch-new-dna-ahmedabad-and-zee-24-kalak-2542970|title=Gujarat CM, Deputy CM launch new DNA Ahmedabad and Zee 24 Kalak|last=|first=|date=2017-09-04|website=[[Zee News|DNA India]]|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-02-25}}</ref>\n*'''Zee Rajasthan:''' Hindi language news channel operating in Rajasthan. It was formerly branded as Zee Marudhara.\n*'''Zee Odisha:''' [[Odia language]] regional news channel. It was formerly branded as Zee Kalinga.\n*'''Zee Salaam:''' [[Urdu]] language news channel.\n*'''Zee Madhya Pradesh Chhattisgarh:''' Hindi language news channel operating in [[Madhya Pradesh]] and [[Chhattisgarh]].\n*'''Zee Punjab Haryana Himachal:''' Hindi language news channel operating in [[Punjab, India|Punjab]], [[Haryana]] and [[Himachal Pradesh]].\n*'''Zee Bihar Jharkhand:''' Hindi and [[Bhojpuri language]] news channel operating in Bihar and Jharkhand.\n*'''Zee Uttar Pradesh Uttarakhand:''' Hindi language news channel operating in [[Uttar Pradesh]] and [[Uttarakhand]].\n\nThe company also runs two regional news channels through its subsidiaries.<ref name=\":1\" /><ref name=\":2\" />\n\n* '''Zee 24 Ghanta:''' 24/7 [[Bengali language]] regional news channel. It is owned by the Zee Akash News Pvt Ltd subsidiary.\n* '''Maurya TV:''' Hindi language news channel operating in [[Bihar]] and [[Jharkhand]]. It is owned by the Maurya TV Pvt Ltd subsidiary.\n\n[[File:DailyNewsandAnalysisCover.jpg|thumb|Cover of ''Daily News & Analysis''.]]\n\n=== Online ===\nZee News operates the Daily News & Analysis and Zee News websites to provide online coverage of the channel. The Zee5 Website which is owned by the [[Zee Entertainment Enterprises]] is used to platform coverage of other ZMCL channels.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.esselgroup.com/zee-media-corporation-limited.html|title=Zee Media Corporation Limited|last=|first=|date=|website=esselgroup.com|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-02-25}}</ref> The World is One News (WION) channel operates its own WION website.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.in/2015/08/18/zee-english-news-channel_n_8002024.html|title=Zee Group To Launch English News Channel, Hires Rohit Gandhi As Editor-In-Chief|last=Basu|first=Indrani|date=2015-08-18|website=[[Huffington Post]]|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-02-25}}</ref> The ZMCL also owns the India.com news website.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.financialexpress.com/industry/cautious-road-ahead-for-zee-entertainment/1787546/|title=Cautious road ahead for Zee Entertainment|last=|first=|date=2019-12-08|website=[[The Financial Express (India)|The Financial Express]]|language=en-US|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-02-25}}</ref>\n\n* '''Zee News Website:''' English and Hindi language online news coverage service of Zee News.\n* '''Daily News & Analysis Website:''' English language online news coverage service. It is branded under the DNA program of Zee News.\n* '''Zee5 Website:''' Streaming service which hosts ZMCL news channels. \n*'''WION Website:''' English language online news coverage service of World is One News.\n*'''India.com:''' English and Hindi language news website owned by ZMCL.\n\n=== Newspaper ===\nThe Daily News & Analysis was an English-language [[broadsheet]] newspaper owned by the Zee Media Corporation Limited. It was launched in 2005 and branded under the Daily News & Analysis (DNA) program of Zee News. It was primarily circulated in [[Mumbai]] and discontinued on 9 October 2019 citing losses.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://theprint.in/india/dna-goes-out-of-print-14-years-after-launch-rise-fall-promising-newspaper/304050/|title=DNA goes out of print 14 years after launch \u2014 rise & sudden fall of a promising newspaper|last=Dutta|first=Amrita Nayak|date=2019-10-11|website=[[ThePrint]]|language=en-US|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-02-25}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chronosphere.biz/IMO/26/imo.html#dna|title=DNA commissions E&Y to certify circulation|author=Bhupesh Trivedi|date=1 June 2006|work=Indian Media Observer (issue #26)|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071219110303/http://www.chronosphere.biz/IMO/26/imo.html#dna|archivedate=19 December 2007|df=dmy}}</ref>\n\n== Controversies ==\n\n=== Jindal Group incident ===\nThe channel was tried for allegedly extorting \u20b9100 [[Crore]] from the [[Jindal Group]] revealed through a sting operation.<ref name=\"The Hindu2\">{{cite news|last=Jebaraj|first=Priscilla|url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/jindal-plays-cd-claims-zee-editors-demanded-rs-100-crore/article4031340.ece|title=Jindal plays CD, claims Zee editors demanded Rs. 100 crore|date=28 July 2016|newspaper=The Hindu|accessdate=4 December 2014|url-status=live}}</ref> Two senior journalists [[Sudhir Chaudhary (journalist)|Sudhir Chaudhary]] and Sameer Ahluwalia were arrested.<ref name=\"NDTV India2\">{{cite news|url=http://www.ndtv.com/article/india/naveen-jindal-vs-zee-senior-journalists-arrested-over-alleged-extortion-298095|title=Naveen Jindal vs Zee: Senior journalists arrested over alleged extortion|accessdate=4 December 2014|publisher=NDTV India}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://m.timesofindia.com/india/Two-Zee-editors-arrested-for-Rs-100-crore-extortion-bid/articleshow/17391903.cms|title=Two Zee editors arrested for 'Rs 100-crore extortion bid' - Times of India|work=The Times of India|access-date=2018-01-30}}</ref><ref name=\"The Australian2\">{{cite news|url=http://www.theaustralian.com.au/news/world/jindal-group-and-zee-television-in-extortion-scandal/story-e6frg6so-1226527713986?nk=e835e32ddf2956600de185626015a1b1|title=Jindal Group and Zee television in extortion scandal|accessdate=4 December 2014|publisher=The Australian}}</ref> [[Naveen Jindal]] had accused the two journalists of trying to extort  {{INRConvert|1,000,000,000||lk=on|year=2011}} in advertisements for Zee News from him through blackmail by threatening to air stories against his company in the [[Coalgate scam]]. Zee News denied the charges and made counter claims of Jindal offering them {{INRConvert|200000000||lk=on|year=2011}}  to halt their investigations against [[Jindal Steel]]'s involvement in the scam but filed no charges.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/business/india-business/Naveen-Jindal-accuses-Zee-News-of-extortion-channel-hits-back/articleshow/16956098.cms|title=Naveen Jindal accuses Zee News of extortion, channel hits back - The Times of India|date=2012-10-25|publisher=Timesofindia.indiatimes.com|accessdate=2012-11-03}}</ref> In July 2018, the Jindal Group withdrew the case against Zee News and both parties to the litigation stated that an out of court settlement had been reached which remains undisclosed.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/india/ed-charges-against-jindal-others-as-his-firm-settles-case-of-extortion-with-zee/|title=ED charges against Naveen Jindal, others as his firm settles case of extortion with Zee|date=2018-07-14|website=The Indian Express|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-12}}</ref>\n\n===Allegations of fabrications===\n\n==== Jawaharlal Nehru University sedition controversy ====\n{{main|2016 JNU sedition controversy}}\n''Zee News'' reported that students from the Democratic Students' Union (DSU) raised \"anti-India\" slogans such as ''Bharat ki barbadi'' (Destruction of India) and ''Pakistan Zindabad'' (Long live Pakistan) in an event on the [[Jawaharlal Nehru University]] campus.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://zeenews.india.com/news/india/from-pakistan-zindabad-to-bharat-ki-barbaadi-slogans-that-were-raised-by-anti-nationals-in-jnu_1855562.html|title=From 'Pakistan Zindabad' to 'Bharat ki barbaadi' - Slogans that were raised by 'anti-nationals' in JNU|date=14 February 2016|newspaper=Zee News}}</ref> In a letter Vishwa Deepak, a journalist working at the channel gave a statement that \"our biases made us hear ''Bhartiya Court Zindabad'' (Long live Indian courts) as ''Pakistan Zindabad.''\" Vishwa Deepak later resigned from the channel after expressing reservations over its \"biased coverage\". The footage on the newscast of Zee News had formed the basis of charges filed by the [[Delhi Police]].<ref name=\"TIE-quit2\">{{cite news|url=http://indianexpress.com/article/india/india-news-india/zee-news-producer-quits-video-we-shot-had-no-pakistan-zindabad-slogan/|title=Zee News producer quits: Video we shot had no Pakistan Zindabad slogan|date=22 February 2016|newspaper=The Indian Express}}</ref> Sudhir Chaudhary, editor and prime time anchor of the channel however on a telecast made a statement saying \"our channel only showed what was happening there, whatever we have shown is 100% authentic.\"<ref name=\"newslaundry-VD2\">{{cite web|url=http://www.newslaundry.com/2016/02/21/we-speak-with-the-zee-news-journalist-who-resigned-over-the-channels-coverage-of-junrow/|title=We speak with the Zee News journalist who resigned over the channel's coverage of #JNURow|date=21 February 2016|newspaper=Newslaundry}}</ref> The forensic report of the Delhi Police however later stated that the footage was doctored.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/india/delhi/story/forensic-experts-say-kanhaiya-video-was-doctored-309626-2016-02-19|title=Forensic experts say Kanhaiya video was doctored|newspaper=India Today|access-date=2019-03-12|agency=Ist|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=|first=|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/india/delhi/story/forensic-experts-say-kanhaiya-video-was-doctored-309626-2016-02-19|title=JNUSU's Kanhaiya Kumar sedition row: 'Raw footage given by TV channel Doctored, finds Forensic Experts'|date=12 June 2016|work=India Today|accessdate=5 March 2019|agency=Express News Service|language=en-IN}}</ref>\n\n==== GPS Chips in \u20b92000 currency notes ====\nAnchor Sudhir Chaudhary ran a Daily News and Analysis program announcing that the [[Indian 2000-rupee note]] issued after [[2016 Indian banknote demonetisation]] by the government have GPS chips which will allow the government to track currency, thereby reducing corruption.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://scroll.in/article/821078/no-the-new-rs-2000-note-will-not-have-a-nano-gps-chip-that-can-track-it-anywhere|title=No, the RBI hasn't announced a Rs 2,000 note with a 'nano GPS chip' that it can track|last=Venkataramakrishnan|first=Rohan|date=9 November 2016|website=Scroll.in|language=en-US|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-02-24}}</ref> The [[Minister of Finance (India)|Minister of Finance]], [[Arun Jaitley]] dismissed the report as being rumours.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ndtv.com/business/nano-chip-in-rs-2-000-notes-arun-jaitley-dismisses-rumours-1623483|title=Nano Chip In Rs 2,000 Notes? Arun Jaitley Dismisses Rumours|website=NDTV.com|access-date=2020-02-24}}</ref> The [[Reserve Bank of India]] has also given a statement that no such chips are present in the currency notes. The report was classified as a [[hoax]] being circulated on social media.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Raghavan|first=TCA Sharad|url=https://www.thehindu.com/business/Economy/No-electronic-chip-in-Rs.-2000-notes-RBI/article16440933.ece|title=No electronic chip in Rs. 2000 notes: RBI|date=2016-11-09|work=The Hindu|access-date=2020-02-24|url-status=live|language=en-IN|issn=0971-751X}}</ref>\n\n==== Navjot Singh Sidhu - Alwar controversy ====\nZee News telecasted a video with the claim that the slogans of ''Pakistan Zindabad'' were raised at a rally in [[Alwar]] presided over by the [[Indian National Congress]] politician, [[Navjot Singh Sidhu]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://zeenews.india.com/video/india/shocking-pak-supporters-shout-pakistan-zindabad-slogan-in-navjot-singh-sidhu-rally-2160544.html|title=Shocking! Pak supporters shout \"Pakistan Zindabad\" slogan in Navjot Singh Sidhu rally|date=2018-12-03|website=Zee News|language=en|access-date=2020-02-24}}</ref> Sidhu accused Zee News of playing a doctored video and threatened to file a defamation suit against Zee News.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/jaipur/to-sue-channel-for-fake-news-sidhu/articleshow/66928000.cms|title=navjot singh sidhu: Will sue channel for fake news: Navjot Singh Sidhu {{!}} Jaipur News - Times of India|last=Mehta|first=Ashish|last2=4 December 2018|date=|website=The Times of India|language=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=24 February 2020|last3=|first3=}}</ref> Sidhu stated that slogans of ''[[Bole So Nihal|Jo Bole So Nihal]]'' were misconstrued as being in favor of Pakistan.<ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://www.business-standard.com/article/current-affairs/sidhu-to-file-defamation-suit-against-tv-channel-for-airing-fake-video-118120301205_1.html|title=Sidhu to file defamation suit against TV channel for airing 'fake' video|date=2018-12-03|work=[[Business Standard]]|access-date=2020-02-24|url-status=live}}</ref> Zee News accused Sidhu of calling a news broadcast to be fake news sent a defamation notice to him. The noticed demanded a apology from him within 24 hours and threatened to pursue legal recourse if an apology was not issued by him.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.freepressjournal.in/cmcm/zee-news-sends-rs-1000-crore-defamation-notice-to-navjot-singh-sidhu-after-he-accuses-channel-of-playing-fake-video|title=Zee News sends Rs 1000 crore defamation notice to Navjot Singh Sidhu after he accuses channel of playing fake video|last=|first=|date=|website=[[Free Press Journal]]|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-02-24}}</ref>\n\n=== Mahua Moitra criminal defamation case ===\nZee News telecasted a show featuring editor-in-chief [[Sudhir Chaudhary (journalist)|Sudhir Chaudhary]] where he claimed that [[Trinamool Congress]] legislator [[Mahua Moitra]] had plagiarised author Martin Longman in her maiden speech after being elected to the [[Lok Sabha]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.altnews.in/zee-news-falsely-claims-mahua-moitra-plagiarised-her-maiden-parliament-speech/|title=Zee News falsely claims Mahua Moitra plagiarised her maiden Parliament speech|last=Chaudhuri|first=Pooja|date=2019-07-03|website=Alt News|language=en-GB|access-date=2020-02-24}}</ref> Moitra accused the channel of false reporting  and submitted a breach of privilege motion against Zee News and Sudhir Chaudhary.<ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://www.business-standard.com/article/news-ani/mahua-moitra-submits-breach-of-privilege-motion-against-zee-tv-ls-speaker-disallows-it-119070400464_1.html|title=Mahua Moitra submits breach of privilege motion against Zee TV, LS speaker disallows it|date=2019-07-04|work=Business Standard|access-date=2020-02-24|url-status=live}}</ref> Martin Longman responded and stated that the legislator did not plagiarise him.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/martin-longman-fascism-article-mahua-moitra-1561305-2019-07-03|title=Trinamool MP Mahua Moitra didn't plagiarise: US writer of fascism article shuts trolls|last=|first=|last2=|first2=|date=3 July 2019|website=[[India Today]]|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-02-24|last3=|first3=}}</ref> Subsequently, Moitra filed a criminal defamation case against Chaudhary.<ref name=\":3\">{{Cite web|url=https://thewire.in/law/mahua-moitra-criminal-defamation-sudhir-chaudhary|title=Mahua Moitra Files Criminal Defamation Case Against Sudhir Chaudhary|last=|first=|date=|website=The Wire|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-02-24}}</ref>\n\n=== Coverage of 2020 Delhi election results ===\nThe [[2020 Delhi Legislative Assembly election]] were held on 8 February 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/elections/assembly-elections/delhi/delhi-election-exit-polls-2020-results-live-news/liveblog/74028057.cms|title=Delhi Election 2020 : Polling held peacefully, counting of votes on February 11|last=|first=|date=|website=[[The Economic Times]]|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref> The exit poll results predicted the [[Aam Aadmi Party]] to retain their government in [[National capital territory of Delhi|National Capital Territory of Delhi]]. The Zee News telecast of the exit poll results featured Sudhir Chaudhary who indulged in polemic commentary against the voters of the election.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://theprint.in/plugged-in/primetime/evm-tampering-in-delhi-across-channels-zees-sudhir-chaudhury-angry-at-voters/362327/|title=EVM tampering in Delhi across channels & Zee's Sudhir Chaudhury angry at voters|last=Jha|first=Fiza|date=2020-02-10|website=[[ThePrint]]|language=en-US|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref> He stated that the people of Delhi had chosen [[Pakistan]] over [[Hindustan]] and that the rule of [[Mughals]] will now return. He further alleged the people of Delhi are lazy and only concerned about \"freebies\" and that issues like [[Ram Janmabhoomi|Ram Mandir]], [[2019 Balakot airstrike|Balakot airstrike]] and [[Article 370 of the Constitution of India|Revocation of Article 370]] do not matter to them which is why they have rejected the [[Bharatiya Janata Party]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.jansatta.com/national/exit-poll-2020-delhi-election-zee-news-tv-anchor-sudhir-chaudhary-after-exit-poll-out-people-not-worried-about-country/1312191/|title=\u0935\u0940\u0921\u093f\u092f\u094b: \u090f\u0917\u094d\u091c\u093f\u091f \u092a\u094b\u0932 \u092e\u0947\u0902 AAP \u0915\u0940 \u091c\u0940\u0924 \u092a\u0930 \u090f\u0902\u0915\u0930 \u0928\u0947 \u0915\u0939\u093e- \u0926\u093f\u0932\u094d\u0932\u0940 \u0915\u094b \u0926\u0947\u0936 \u091f\u0942\u091f\u0928\u0947 \u0915\u0940 \u091a\u093f\u0902\u0924\u093e \u0928\u0939\u0940\u0902|last=|first=|date=2020-02-09|website=[[Jansatta]]|language=hi|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref> The telecast resulted in backlash and mockery of Zee News and Sudhir Chaudhary on social media.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.freepressjournal.in/india/how-does-this-qualify-as-journalism-twitter-mocks-zee-news-and-sudhir-chaudhary-for-blaming-delhi-voters-after-exit-polls|title='How does this qualify as journalism?': Twitter mocks Zee News and Sudhir Chaudhary for blaming Delhi voters after exit polls|last=|first=|date=9 February 2020|website=[[Free Press Journal]]|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n\n* [[Sudarshan News]]\n*[[ZEE5]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.zeemedia.in Company website]\n* [https://zeenews.india.com/ Channel website]\n\n{{Essel Group}}\n{{Television news in India}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Zee News}}\n[[Category:24-hour television news channels in India]]\n[[Category:Television channels and stations established in 1999]]\n[[Category:Hindi-language television channels in India]]\n[[Category:Hindi-language television stations]]\n[[Category:Essel Group]]\n[[Category:Zee Entertainment Enterprises]]\n[[Category:Media companies of India]]\n[[Category:Entertainment companies of India]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use Indian English|date=May 2015}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2015}}\n{{See also|Zee TV}}\n{{Infobox TV channel\n| launch         = {{Launch date and age|df=y|1999|08|27}}\n| logofile        =Zee News.png\n| logoalt          = \n| owner          = [[Essel Group]]\n| headquarters   =[[Noida]], [[Uttar Pradesh]], [[India]]\n| country        = [[India]]\n| language       = [[Hindi]]\n| picture format = [[1080i]] [[HDTV]]<br />{{small|(downscaled to [[4:3]] [[576i]] for the [[SDTV]] feed)}}\n| broadcast area = International\n| share             =  \n| share as of       = \n| share source      =   \n| sister names = [[Zee TV]]\n| terr serv 1      = [[Oqaab]]<br/>(Afghanistan)\n| terr chan 1      = Channel 45\n| sat serv 1 = [[Airtel Digital TV]]\n| sat chan 1 = Channel 311\n| sat serv 2 = [[Dish TV]]\n| sat chan 2 = Channel 651\n| sat serv 3 = [[Reliance Digital TV]]\n| sat chan 3 = Channel 408\n| sat serv 4 = [[Tata Sky]]\n| sat chan 4 =  Channel 511\n| sat serv 5 = [[Videocon D2H]]\n| sat chan 5 = Channel 302\n| cable serv 1 = [[Siti Cable]]\n| cable chan 1 = Channel 303\n| cable serv 2 = [[Cable TV Hong Kong]]\n| cable chan 2 = Channel 852\n| adsl serv 1 = [[Now TV (China)|now TV]]<br/>(Hong Kong)\n| adsl chan 1 = Channel 785\n| adsl serv 2 = [[Dish Network]]<br/>(United States)\n| adsl chan 2 = Channel 708 (SD)\n| online serv 1    = Live Stream (International)\n| online chan 1    = [http://zeenews.india.com/live-tv live Web stream at Zee News]\n| name = Zee News\n| website = {{URL|https://zeenews.india.com/}}\n| logocaption = \n| logosize =190px \n}}\n\n'''Zee News''' is a [[Hindi language|Hindi-language]] news channel owned by the [[Essel Group]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.esselgroup.com/zee-media-corporation-limited.html|title=Our Companies: Zee Media Corporation Limited|last=|first=|date=|website=esselgroup.com|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-02-25}}</ref> It is associated with several other sister news channels which provide coverage in Hindi, English and several regional languages of India. Zee News was launched on 27 August 1999 as Zee Sports Ltd. The company was [[Certificate of incorporation|reincorporated]] on 27 May 2004 as Zee News Ltd.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://www.business-standard.com/company/zee-media-27705/information/company-history|title=Zee Media Corporation Ltd.|date=|work=[[Business Standard]]|access-date=2020-02-25|url-status=live}}</ref> In 2013, Zee News Ltd changed its name to Zee Media Corporation Limited.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/zee-media-corporation-ltd/infocompanyhistory/companyid-18879.cms|title=Zee Media Corporation History {{!}} Zee Media Corporation Information|last=|first=|date=|website=[[The Economic Times]]|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-02-25}}</ref> The Zee News channel is the flagship channel of the company.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ndtv.com/business/stock/zee-media-corporation-ltd_zeenews/reports-directors-report|title=Director Reports, Company Results of Zee Media Corp|last=|first=|date=|website=[[NDTV Profit]]|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-02-25}}</ref>\n\nThe chairman of the group is [[Subhash Chandra]], who is a [[Bharatiya Janata Party]]-backed member of the [[Rajya Sabha]].<ref>{{Cite news|last=Mohan|first=Archis|url=https://www.business-standard.com/article/politics/subhash-chandra-bets-on-bjp-support-for-rajya-sabha-entry-116053101457_1.html|title=Subhash Chandra bets on BJP support for Rajya Sabha entry|date=2016-06-01|work=Business Standard India|access-date=2020-02-24}}</ref> [[Sudhir Chaudhary (journalist)|Sudhir Chaudhary]] is the editor-in-chief of Zee News and the anchor of the prime time show on the channel.<ref name=\"exch1\">{{cite web|url=http://www.exchange4media.mobi/tv/sudhir-chaudhary-now-also-editor-in-chief-of-zee-business_68276.html|title=Sudhir Chaudhary now also editor in Chief of zee business|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://archive.today/20170715163422/http://www.exchange4media.mobi/tv/sudhir-chaudhary-now-also-editor-in-chief-of-zee-business_68276.html|archive-date=15 July 2017|access-date=15 July 2017|df=}}</ref> The channel has been involved in several controversies and has broadcast fabricated news stories on multiple occasions.<ref name=\"fake\">List of sources:\n\n* {{Cite web|url=https://www.nationalheraldindia.com/book-extract/book-extract-republic-tv-age-of-fake-news-and-promoters-in-indian-tv-newsrooms|title=Book extract: Republic TV, age of fake news and promoters in Indian TV newsrooms|last=Bhushan|first=Sandeep|date=2019-06-29|website=[[National Herald (India)|National Herald]]|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-02-25}}\n* {{Cite web|url=https://www.thehindubusinessline.com/blink/read/the-troubling-association-of-zee-and-jlf/article30693362.ece|title=The festival and its funder|last=Jha|first=Aditya Mani|date=2020-01-31|website=[[Business Line]]|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-02-25}}\n* {{Cite web|url=https://www.altnews.in/zee-news-broadcasts-old-unrelated-satellite-visuals-as-destroyed-jem-camp-in-balakot/|title=Zee News broadcasts old, unrelated satellite visuals as destroyed JEM camp in Balakot|last=Patel|first=Jignesh|date=2019-03-08|website=[[Alt News]]|language=en-GB|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-02-25}}\n* {{Cite web|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/india/india-news-india/zee-news-producer-quits-video-we-shot-had-no-pakistan-zindabad-slogan/|title=Zee News producer quits: Video we shot had no Pakistan Zindabad slogan|last=Hafeez|first=Sarah|date=2018-02-22|website=[[The Indian Express]]|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-02-25}}\n* {{Cite web|url=https://www.outlookindia.com/magazine/story/india-news-are-newsrooms-run-by-political-masters-why-are-editors-compromising-on-truth-telling/302846|title=Are Newsrooms Run By Political Masters? Why Are Editors Compromising On Truth Telling?|last=Yadav|first=Puneet|date=2020-02-21|website=[[Outlook (Indian magazine)|Outlook]]|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-02-25}}\n* {{Cite web|url=https://theprint.in/hoaxposed/zee-news-tweets-doctored-video-of-navjot-sidhus-rajasthan-rally/158011/|title=Zee News tweets doctored video of Navjot Sidhu\u2019s Rajasthan rally|last=Rampal|first=Nikhil|date=2018-12-03|website=[[ThePrint]]|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-02-25}}\n* {{Cite web|url=http://www.catchnews.com/politics-news/saffron-journalism-zee-news-and-art-of-manufacturing-anti-nationals-1457687402.html|title=Saffron journalism: Zee News & art of manufacturing anti-nationals|last=Menon|first=Aditya|date=10 February 2017|website=catchnews.com|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-02-25}}\n* {{Cite web|url=https://www.dailyo.in/politics/zee-news-subhash-chandra-sudhir-chaudhary-narendra-modi-bhakt-sangh-jnu-bjp-muslims-pakistan-anupam-kher/story/1/9474.html|title=Subhash Chandra failed to convince Zee is not Modi's mouthpiece|last=Khan|first=Saif Ahmed|date=2016-03-10|website=[[India Today|DailyO]]|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-02-25}}</ref> The channel is subjected to an ongoing criminal defamation case against legislator [[Mahua Moitra]] as of March 2020.<ref name=\":3\" />\n\n== Outlets ==\n\n=== Television ===\nThe Zee Media Corporation Limited (ZMCL) operates a number of other channels, some in regional languages with the stated intent of providing a pan-Indian reach.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://in.reuters.com/finance/stocks/company-profile/ZEEN.BO|title=Profile: Zee Media Corporation Ltd (ZEEN.BO)|last=|first=|date=|website=[[Reuters]]|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-02-25}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.moneycontrol.com/news/business/companies/zee-media-to-foray-into-english-news-broadcasting-1512583.html|title=Zee Media to foray into English news broadcasting|last=|first=|date=17 August 2015|website=[[Moneycontrol]]|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-02-25}}</ref><ref name=\":0\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.zeemedia.in/channeloverview.html|title=ZMCL Channels Overview|last=|first=|date=|website=www.zeemedia.in|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-02-25}}</ref>\n\n* '''World is One News (WION):''' [[English language]] news channel.\n* '''Zee Business:''' Hindi language business news channel.\n*'''Zee Hindustan:''' 24/7 national Hindi language news channel. It was relaunched in 2017 as an anchor-less news channel.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.exchange4media.com/media-tv-news/zee-hindustan-re-launched-as-anchor-less-channel-93472.html|title=Zee Hindustan re-launched as anchor-less channel - Exchange4media|last=|first=|date=|website=exchange4media.com|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-02-25}}</ref> It was formerly branded as Zee Sangam and India 24x7.<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=https://bestmediainfo.com/2017/05/india-24x7-is-now-zee-hindustan/|title=India 24x7 is now Zee Hindustan|last=|first=|last2=|date=23 May 2017|website=Best Media Info|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-02-25|last3=}}</ref>\n* '''[[Zee 24 Taas]]:''' 24/7 [[Marathi language]] regional news channel.\n*'''Zee 24 Kalak:''' 24/7 [[Gujarati language]] regional news channel. It was inaugurated on 20 August 2017 by [[Vijay Rupani]], the [[Chief minister (India)|Chief Minister]] of Gujarat.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dnaindia.com/india/report-gujarat-cm-deputy-cm-launch-new-dna-ahmedabad-and-zee-24-kalak-2542970|title=Gujarat CM, Deputy CM launch new DNA Ahmedabad and Zee 24 Kalak|last=|first=|date=2017-09-04|website=[[Zee News|DNA India]]|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-02-25}}</ref>\n*'''Zee Rajasthan:''' Hindi language news channel operating in Rajasthan. It was formerly branded as Zee Marudhara.\n*'''Zee Odisha:''' [[Odia language]] regional news channel. It was formerly branded as Zee Kalinga.\n*'''Zee Salaam:''' [[Urdu]] language news channel.\n*'''Zee Madhya Pradesh Chhattisgarh:''' Hindi language news channel operating in [[Madhya Pradesh]] and [[Chhattisgarh]].\n*'''Zee Punjab Haryana Himachal:''' Hindi language news channel operating in [[Punjab, India|Punjab]], [[Haryana]] and [[Himachal Pradesh]].\n*'''Zee Bihar Jharkhand:''' Hindi and [[Bhojpuri language]] news channel operating in Bihar and Jharkhand.\n*'''Zee Uttar Pradesh Uttarakhand:''' Hindi language news channel operating in [[Uttar Pradesh]] and [[Uttarakhand]].\n\nThe company also runs two regional news channels through its subsidiaries.<ref name=\":1\" /><ref name=\":2\" />\n\n* '''Zee 24 Ghanta:''' 24/7 [[Bengali language]] regional news channel. It is owned by the Zee Akash News Pvt Ltd subsidiary.\n* '''Maurya TV:''' Hindi language news channel operating in [[Bihar]] and [[Jharkhand]]. It is owned by the Maurya TV Pvt Ltd subsidiary.\n\n[[File:DailyNewsandAnalysisCover.jpg|thumb|Cover of ''Daily News & Analysis''.]]\n\n=== Online ===\nZee News operates the Daily News & Analysis and Zee News websites to provide online coverage of the channel. The Zee5 Website which is owned by the [[Zee Entertainment Enterprises]] is used to platform coverage of other ZMCL channels.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.esselgroup.com/zee-media-corporation-limited.html|title=Zee Media Corporation Limited|last=|first=|date=|website=esselgroup.com|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-02-25}}</ref> The World is One News (WION) channel operates its own WION website.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.in/2015/08/18/zee-english-news-channel_n_8002024.html|title=Zee Group To Launch English News Channel, Hires Rohit Gandhi As Editor-In-Chief|last=Basu|first=Indrani|date=2015-08-18|website=[[Huffington Post]]|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-02-25}}</ref> The ZMCL also owns the India.com news website.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.financialexpress.com/industry/cautious-road-ahead-for-zee-entertainment/1787546/|title=Cautious road ahead for Zee Entertainment|last=|first=|date=2019-12-08|website=[[The Financial Express (India)|The Financial Express]]|language=en-US|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-02-25}}</ref>\n\n* '''Zee News Website:''' English and Hindi language online news coverage service of Zee News.\n* '''Daily News & Analysis Website:''' English language online news coverage service. It is branded under the DNA program of Zee News.\n* '''Zee5 Website:''' Streaming service which hosts ZMCL news channels. \n*'''WION Website:''' English language online news coverage service of World is One News.\n*'''India.com:''' English and Hindi language news website owned by ZMCL.\n\n=== Newspaper ===\nThe Daily News & Analysis was an English-language [[broadsheet]] newspaper owned by the Zee Media Corporation Limited. It was launched in 2005 and branded under the Daily News & Analysis (DNA) program of Zee News. It was primarily circulated in [[Mumbai]] and discontinued on 9 October 2019 citing losses.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://theprint.in/india/dna-goes-out-of-print-14-years-after-launch-rise-fall-promising-newspaper/304050/|title=DNA goes out of print 14 years after launch \u2014 rise & sudden fall of a promising newspaper|last=Dutta|first=Amrita Nayak|date=2019-10-11|website=[[ThePrint]]|language=en-US|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-02-25}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chronosphere.biz/IMO/26/imo.html#dna|title=DNA commissions E&Y to certify circulation|author=Bhupesh Trivedi|date=1 June 2006|work=Indian Media Observer (issue #26)|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071219110303/http://www.chronosphere.biz/IMO/26/imo.html#dna|archivedate=19 December 2007|df=dmy}}</ref>\n\n== Controversies ==\n\n=== Jindal Group incident ===\nThe channel was tried for allegedly extorting \u20b9100 [[Crore]] from the [[Jindal Group]] revealed through a sting operation.<ref name=\"The Hindu2\">{{cite news|last=Jebaraj|first=Priscilla|url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/jindal-plays-cd-claims-zee-editors-demanded-rs-100-crore/article4031340.ece|title=Jindal plays CD, claims Zee editors demanded Rs. 100 crore|date=28 July 2016|newspaper=The Hindu|accessdate=4 December 2014|url-status=live}}</ref> Two senior journalists [[Sudhir Chaudhary (journalist)|Sudhir Chaudhary]] and Sameer Ahluwalia were arrested.<ref name=\"NDTV India2\">{{cite news|url=http://www.ndtv.com/article/india/naveen-jindal-vs-zee-senior-journalists-arrested-over-alleged-extortion-298095|title=Naveen Jindal vs Zee: Senior journalists arrested over alleged extortion|accessdate=4 December 2014|publisher=NDTV India}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://m.timesofindia.com/india/Two-Zee-editors-arrested-for-Rs-100-crore-extortion-bid/articleshow/17391903.cms|title=Two Zee editors arrested for 'Rs 100-crore extortion bid' - Times of India|work=The Times of India|access-date=2018-01-30}}</ref><ref name=\"The Australian2\">{{cite news|url=http://www.theaustralian.com.au/news/world/jindal-group-and-zee-television-in-extortion-scandal/story-e6frg6so-1226527713986?nk=e835e32ddf2956600de185626015a1b1|title=Jindal Group and Zee television in extortion scandal|accessdate=4 December 2014|publisher=The Australian}}</ref> [[Naveen Jindal]] had accused the two journalists of trying to extort  {{INRConvert|1,000,000,000||lk=on|year=2011}} in advertisements for Zee News from him through blackmail by threatening to air stories against his company in the [[Coalgate scam]]. Zee News denied the charges and made counter claims of Jindal offering them {{INRConvert|200000000||lk=on|year=2011}}  to halt their investigations against [[Jindal Steel]]'s involvement in the scam but filed no charges.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/business/india-business/Naveen-Jindal-accuses-Zee-News-of-extortion-channel-hits-back/articleshow/16956098.cms|title=Naveen Jindal accuses Zee News of extortion, channel hits back - The Times of India|date=2012-10-25|publisher=Timesofindia.indiatimes.com|accessdate=2012-11-03}}</ref> In July 2018, the Jindal Group withdrew the case against Zee News and both parties to the litigation stated that an out of court settlement had been reached which remains undisclosed.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/india/ed-charges-against-jindal-others-as-his-firm-settles-case-of-extortion-with-zee/|title=ED charges against Naveen Jindal, others as his firm settles case of extortion with Zee|date=2018-07-14|website=The Indian Express|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-12}}</ref>\n\n===Allegations of fabrications===\n\n==== Jawaharlal Nehru University sedition controversy ====\n{{main|2016 JNU sedition controversy}}\n''Zee News'' reported that students from the Democratic Students' Union (DSU) raised \"anti-India\" slogans such as ''Bharat ki barbadi'' (Destruction of India) and ''Pakistan Zindabad'' (Long live Pakistan) in an event on the [[Jawaharlal Nehru University]] campus.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://zeenews.india.com/news/india/from-pakistan-zindabad-to-bharat-ki-barbaadi-slogans-that-were-raised-by-anti-nationals-in-jnu_1855562.html|title=From 'Pakistan Zindabad' to 'Bharat ki barbaadi' - Slogans that were raised by 'anti-nationals' in JNU|date=14 February 2016|newspaper=Zee News}}</ref> In a letter Vishwa Deepak, a journalist working at the channel gave a statement that \"our biases made us hear ''Bhartiya Court Zindabad'' (Long live Indian courts) as ''Pakistan Zindabad.''\" Vishwa Deepak later resigned from the channel after expressing reservations over its \"biased coverage\". The footage on the newscast of Zee News had formed the basis of charges filed by the [[Delhi Police]].<ref name=\"TIE-quit2\">{{cite news|url=http://indianexpress.com/article/india/india-news-india/zee-news-producer-quits-video-we-shot-had-no-pakistan-zindabad-slogan/|title=Zee News producer quits: Video we shot had no Pakistan Zindabad slogan|date=22 February 2016|newspaper=The Indian Express}}</ref> Sudhir Chaudhary, editor and prime time anchor of the channel however on a telecast made a statement saying \"our channel only showed what was happening there, whatever we have shown is 100% authentic.\"<ref name=\"newslaundry-VD2\">{{cite web|url=http://www.newslaundry.com/2016/02/21/we-speak-with-the-zee-news-journalist-who-resigned-over-the-channels-coverage-of-junrow/|title=We speak with the Zee News journalist who resigned over the channel's coverage of #JNURow|date=21 February 2016|newspaper=Newslaundry}}</ref> The forensic report of the Delhi Police however later stated that the footage was doctored.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/india/delhi/story/forensic-experts-say-kanhaiya-video-was-doctored-309626-2016-02-19|title=Forensic experts say Kanhaiya video was doctored|newspaper=India Today|access-date=2019-03-12|agency=Ist|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=|first=|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/india/delhi/story/forensic-experts-say-kanhaiya-video-was-doctored-309626-2016-02-19|title=JNUSU's Kanhaiya Kumar sedition row: 'Raw footage given by TV channel Doctored, finds Forensic Experts'|date=12 June 2016|work=India Today|accessdate=5 March 2019|agency=Express News Service|language=en-IN}}</ref>\n\n==== GPS Chips in \u20b92000 currency notes ====\nAnchor Sudhir Chaudhary ran a Daily News and Analysis program announcing that the [[Indian 2000-rupee note]] issued after [[2016 Indian banknote demonetisation]] by the government have GPS chips which will allow the government to track currency, thereby reducing corruption.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://scroll.in/article/821078/no-the-new-rs-2000-note-will-not-have-a-nano-gps-chip-that-can-track-it-anywhere|title=No, the RBI hasn't announced a Rs 2,000 note with a 'nano GPS chip' that it can track|last=Venkataramakrishnan|first=Rohan|date=9 November 2016|website=Scroll.in|language=en-US|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-02-24}}</ref> The [[Minister of Finance (India)|Minister of Finance]], [[Arun Jaitley]] dismissed the report as being rumours.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ndtv.com/business/nano-chip-in-rs-2-000-notes-arun-jaitley-dismisses-rumours-1623483|title=Nano Chip In Rs 2,000 Notes? Arun Jaitley Dismisses Rumours|website=NDTV.com|access-date=2020-02-24}}</ref> The [[Reserve Bank of India]] has also given a statement that no such chips are present in the currency notes. The report was classified as a [[hoax]] being circulated on social media.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Raghavan|first=TCA Sharad|url=https://www.thehindu.com/business/Economy/No-electronic-chip-in-Rs.-2000-notes-RBI/article16440933.ece|title=No electronic chip in Rs. 2000 notes: RBI|date=2016-11-09|work=The Hindu|access-date=2020-02-24|url-status=live|language=en-IN|issn=0971-751X}}</ref>\n\n==== Navjot Singh Sidhu - Alwar controversy ====\nZee News telecasted a video with the claim that the slogans of ''Pakistan Zindabad'' were raised at a rally in [[Alwar]] presided over by the [[Indian National Congress]] politician, [[Navjot Singh Sidhu]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://zeenews.india.com/video/india/shocking-pak-supporters-shout-pakistan-zindabad-slogan-in-navjot-singh-sidhu-rally-2160544.html|title=Shocking! Pak supporters shout \"Pakistan Zindabad\" slogan in Navjot Singh Sidhu rally|date=2018-12-03|website=Zee News|language=en|access-date=2020-02-24}}</ref> Sidhu accused Zee News of playing a doctored video and threatened to file a defamation suit against Zee News.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/jaipur/to-sue-channel-for-fake-news-sidhu/articleshow/66928000.cms|title=navjot singh sidhu: Will sue channel for fake news: Navjot Singh Sidhu {{!}} Jaipur News - Times of India|last=Mehta|first=Ashish|last2=4 December 2018|date=|website=The Times of India|language=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=24 February 2020|last3=|first3=}}</ref> Sidhu stated that slogans of ''[[Bole So Nihal|Jo Bole So Nihal]]'' were misconstrued as being in favor of Pakistan.<ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://www.business-standard.com/article/current-affairs/sidhu-to-file-defamation-suit-against-tv-channel-for-airing-fake-video-118120301205_1.html|title=Sidhu to file defamation suit against TV channel for airing 'fake' video|date=2018-12-03|work=[[Business Standard]]|access-date=2020-02-24|url-status=live}}</ref> Zee News accused Sidhu of calling a news broadcast to be fake news sent a defamation notice to him. The noticed demanded a apology from him within 24 hours and threatened to pursue legal recourse if an apology was not issued by him.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.freepressjournal.in/cmcm/zee-news-sends-rs-1000-crore-defamation-notice-to-navjot-singh-sidhu-after-he-accuses-channel-of-playing-fake-video|title=Zee News sends Rs 1000 crore defamation notice to Navjot Singh Sidhu after he accuses channel of playing fake video|last=|first=|date=|website=[[Free Press Journal]]|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-02-24}}</ref>\n\n=== Mahua Moitra criminal defamation case ===\nZee News telecasted a show featuring editor-in-chief [[Sudhir Chaudhary (journalist)|Sudhir Chaudhary]] where he claimed that [[Trinamool Congress]] legislator [[Mahua Moitra]] had plagiarised author Martin Longman in her maiden speech after being elected to the [[Lok Sabha]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.altnews.in/zee-news-falsely-claims-mahua-moitra-plagiarised-her-maiden-parliament-speech/|title=Zee News falsely claims Mahua Moitra plagiarised her maiden Parliament speech|last=Chaudhuri|first=Pooja|date=2019-07-03|website=Alt News|language=en-GB|access-date=2020-02-24}}</ref> Moitra accused the channel of false reporting  and submitted a breach of privilege motion against Zee News and Sudhir Chaudhary.<ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://www.business-standard.com/article/news-ani/mahua-moitra-submits-breach-of-privilege-motion-against-zee-tv-ls-speaker-disallows-it-119070400464_1.html|title=Mahua Moitra submits breach of privilege motion against Zee TV, LS speaker disallows it|date=2019-07-04|work=Business Standard|access-date=2020-02-24|url-status=live}}</ref> Martin Longman responded and stated that the legislator did not plagarise him.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/martin-longman-fascism-article-mahua-moitra-1561305-2019-07-03|title=Trinamool MP Mahua Moitra didn't plagiarise: US writer of fascism article shuts trolls|last=|first=|last2=|first2=|date=3 July 2019|website=[[India Today]]|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-02-24|last3=|first3=}}</ref> Subsequently, Moitra filed a criminal defamation case against Chaudhary.<ref name=\":3\">{{Cite web|url=https://thewire.in/law/mahua-moitra-criminal-defamation-sudhir-chaudhary|title=Mahua Moitra Files Criminal Defamation Case Against Sudhir Chaudhary|last=|first=|date=|website=The Wire|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-02-24}}</ref>\n\n=== Coverage of 2020 Delhi election results ===\nThe [[2020 Delhi Legislative Assembly election]] were held on 8 February 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/elections/assembly-elections/delhi/delhi-election-exit-polls-2020-results-live-news/liveblog/74028057.cms|title=Delhi Election 2020 : Polling held peacefully, counting of votes on February 11|last=|first=|date=|website=[[The Economic Times]]|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref> The exit poll results predicted the [[Aam Aadmi Party]] to retain their government in [[National capital territory of Delhi|National Capital Territory of Delhi]]. The Zee News telecast of the exit poll results featured Sudhir Chaudhary who indulged in polemic commentary against the voters of the election.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://theprint.in/plugged-in/primetime/evm-tampering-in-delhi-across-channels-zees-sudhir-chaudhury-angry-at-voters/362327/|title=EVM tampering in Delhi across channels & Zee's Sudhir Chaudhury angry at voters|last=Jha|first=Fiza|date=2020-02-10|website=[[ThePrint]]|language=en-US|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref> He stated that the people of Delhi had chosen [[Pakistan]] over [[Hindustan]] and that the rule of [[Mughals]] will now return. He further alleged the people of Delhi are lazy and only concerned about \"freebies\" and that issues like [[Ram Janmabhoomi|Ram Mandir]], [[2019 Balakot airstrike|Balakot airstrike]] and [[Article 370 of the Constitution of India|Revocation of Article 370]] do not matter to them which is why they have rejected the [[Bharatiya Janata Party]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.jansatta.com/national/exit-poll-2020-delhi-election-zee-news-tv-anchor-sudhir-chaudhary-after-exit-poll-out-people-not-worried-about-country/1312191/|title=\u0935\u0940\u0921\u093f\u092f\u094b: \u090f\u0917\u094d\u091c\u093f\u091f \u092a\u094b\u0932 \u092e\u0947\u0902 AAP \u0915\u0940 \u091c\u0940\u0924 \u092a\u0930 \u090f\u0902\u0915\u0930 \u0928\u0947 \u0915\u0939\u093e- \u0926\u093f\u0932\u094d\u0932\u0940 \u0915\u094b \u0926\u0947\u0936 \u091f\u0942\u091f\u0928\u0947 \u0915\u0940 \u091a\u093f\u0902\u0924\u093e \u0928\u0939\u0940\u0902|last=|first=|date=2020-02-09|website=[[Jansatta]]|language=hi|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref> The telecast resulted in backlash and mockery of Zee News and Sudhir Chaudhary on social media.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.freepressjournal.in/india/how-does-this-qualify-as-journalism-twitter-mocks-zee-news-and-sudhir-chaudhary-for-blaming-delhi-voters-after-exit-polls|title='How does this qualify as journalism?': Twitter mocks Zee News and Sudhir Chaudhary for blaming Delhi voters after exit polls|last=|first=|date=9 February 2020|website=[[Free Press Journal]]|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n\n* [[Sudarshan News]]\n*[[ZEE5]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n==External links==\n* [http://www.zeemedia.in Company website]\n* [https://zeenews.india.com/ Channel website]\n\n{{Essel Group}}\n{{Television news in India}} \n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Zee News}}\n[[Category:24-hour television news channels in India]]\n[[Category:Television channels and stations established in 1999]]\n[[Category:Hindi-language television channels in India]]\n[[Category:Hindi-language television stations]]\n[[Category:Essel Group]]\n[[Category:Zee Entertainment Enterprises]]\n[[Category:Media companies of India]]\n[[Category:Entertainment companies of India]]\n", "name_user": "John of Reading", "label": "safe", "comment": "Typo/generalfixes, replaced: plagarise \u2192 plagiarise", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Zee_News"}
{"title_page": "Andrew Murray (trade unionist)", "text_new": "{{other people||Andrew Murray (disambiguation)}}\n{{EngvarB|date=August 2014}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2014}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| honorific-prefix   = \n| name               = Andrew Murray\n| honorific-suffix   = \n| image              = \n| imagesize          = \n| smallimage         =\n| alt                = \n| caption            = \n| office             = [[Special advisers (UK government)|Special Political Advisor]]<br />for the [[Her Majesty's Most Loyal Opposition (United Kingdom)|Leader of the Opposition]] \n| leader             = [[Jeremy Corbyn]]\n| term_start         = 26 February 2018\n| term_end           = 18 February 2020<ref>{{cite news |last1=Payne |first1=Sebastian |last2=Pickard |first2=Jim |title=Andrew Murray quits as adviser to Jeremy Corbyn |url=https://www.ft.com/content/dc552842-5289-11ea-8841-482eed0038b1 |accessdate=19 February 2020 |work=Financial Times}}</ref>\n| predecessor        = ''Position established''\n| successor          = \n| office1            = Chair of the [[Stop the War Coalition]]\n| deputy1            = [[Chris Nineham]]\n| president2         = [[Tony Benn]]\n| deputy2            = [[Chris Nineham]]\n| term_start2        = 21 September 2001\n| term_end2          = 14 June 2011\n| majority2          = \n| predecessor2       = ''Position established''\n| successor2         = [[Jeremy Corbyn]]\n| office2            =\n| term_start1        = 12 September 2015\n| term_end1          = 12 October 2016\n| majority1          = \n| predecessor1       = [[Jeremy Corbyn]]\n| successor1         = [[Murad Qureshi]]\n| office3            = [[Chief of Staff]] of [[Unite the Union]]\n| 1blankname3        = {{nowrap|General Secretary}}\n| 1namedata3         = [[Len McCluskey]]  \n| term_start3        = 1 January 2011\n| term_end3          = \n| majority3          = \n| predecessor3       =\n| successor3         = \n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|1958|7|3|df=yes}}\n| birth_place        = \n| death_date         =\n| death_place        = \n| restingplace       = \n| restingplacecoordinates = \n| birthname          = Andrew Philip Drummond-Murray\n| citizenship        = \n| nationality        = \n| party              = [[Labour Party (UK)|Labour Party]] (2016\u2013present)\n| otherparty         = [[Communist Party of Great Britain]] (1976\u20131991)<br />[[Communist Party of Britain]] (1995\u20132016)\n| spouse             = [[Susan Michie]] (1981\u20131997)<br />Anna Kruthoffer (2003\u2013present)\n| partner            =\n| relations          = [[Arthur Hope, 2nd Baron Rankeillour]]<br /><small>(maternal grandfather)</small>\n| children           = \n| parents            = [[Peter Drummond-Murray of Mastrick]]<br />Hon. Barbara Mary Hope\n| residence          = \n| education          = [[Worth School]]\n| alma_mater         =\n| occupation         = Trade union official\n| cabinet            = \n| committees         = [[General Council of the Trades Union Congress]] (2011\u2013present)<br />Executive Committee of the Communist Party of Britain (2000\u20132004, 2008\u20132011)\n| portfolio          = \n| religion           = \n| signature          = \n| signature_alt      = \n| website            = \n| footnotes          = \n}}\n\n'''Andrew Philip Drummond-Murray''' (born 3 July 1958),<ref name=\"ThePeerage\">{{cite news|url=http://www.thepeerage.com/p19.htm#i182|title=Person Page - 19|website=The Peerage|date=23 May 2015|accessdate=17 May 2017}}</ref> commonly known as '''Andrew Murray''', is a British trade union and Labour Party official, and activist. Murray was seconded from Unite to Labour headquarters for the [[2017 United Kingdom general election|2017 general election]], subsequently becoming an adviser to [[Jeremy Corbyn]].\n\nBorn into an aristocratic Scottish family, Murray began his career as a journalist and later became a senior official for various trade unions.<ref>https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2018/dec/16/why-are-labour-party-leaders-so-quiet-on-europe---maybe-it-is-the-lure-of-disaster?CMP=share_btn_tw</ref>\n\nAfter forty years in the [[Communist Party of Great Britain]] (CPGB) and then the [[Communist Party of Britain]], he joined the [[Labour Party (UK)|Labour Party]] towards the end of 2016.<ref name=\"Maguire\">{{cite news|last=Maguire|first=Kevin|url=http://www.newstatesman.com/politics/uk/2016/11/commons-confidential-murray-comes-cold|title=Commons Confidential: Murray comes in from the cold|work=New Statesman|date=25 November 2016|accessdate=15 May 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"Boffey\">{{cite news|last=Boffey|first=Daniel|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2016/dec/10/unite-leaders-aide-andrew-murray-leaves-communist-party-to-join-labour|title=Unite leader's aide leaves Communist party to join Labour|work=The Observer|date=10 December 2016|accessdate=10 December 2016}}</ref> He was chair of the [[Stop the War Coalition]] from its formation in 2001 until June 2011, and again from September 2015 to 2016.\n\nHe is a contributor to the ''[[Morning Star (British newspaper)|Morning Star]]'' and ''[[Tribune (magazine)|Tribune]]''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://tribunemag.co.uk/author/andrew-murray|title=Andrew Murray|website=tribunemag.co.uk|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-12}}</ref><!-- Murray is certainly no longer chair, and Murad Qureshi appears to have replaced him, but sources are vague. -->\n\n==Biography==\n===Education and journalism===\n[[File:Main building at Worth School.jpg|thumb|left|200px|Worth School]]\nMurray was born in 1958 to [[Peter Drummond-Murray of Mastrick]], a [[stockbroker]] and banker who was [[Slains Pursuivant]] from 1981 to 2009, and [[The Honourable]] Barbara Mary Hope, daughter of former Conservative MP and governor of the [[Madras Presidency]] in [[British India]] from 1940 to 1946 [[Arthur Hope, 2nd Baron Rankeillour|Lord Rankeillour]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/peter-drummond-murray-8crb3gxln9k|title=Peter Drummond Murray|work=The Times|location=London|date=13 May 2014|accessdate=17 May 2017}} {{subscription required}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thepeerage.com/p5711.htm#i57103|title=Person Page - 5711: William Edward Peter Louis Drummond-Murray|website=The Peerage|agency=Burke's Peerage|date=14 May 2017|accessdate=17 May 2017}}</ref> He was  educated at [[Worth School]], a Benedictine independent boarding school in Sussex.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thepeerage.com/p19.htm#i182|title=Person Page - 19: Andrew Philip Drummond-Murray|website=The Peerage|agency=Burke's Peerage|date=23 May 2015|accessdate=17 May 2017}}</ref> Murray left school at 16 with 4 [[GCE Ordinary Level (United Kingdom)|'O' levels]].\n\nAfter working as a messenger at ''[[Reader's Digest]]'' and a copy boy for the ''[[The New York Times International Edition|International Herald Tribune]]'', he undertook journalism training at the ''Sussex Express''.<ref name=\"EatonWilbyBushMaguireChakelian\">{{cite news|last1=Eaton|first1=George|last2=Wilby|first2=Peter|last3=Bush|first3=Stephen|last4=Maguire|first4=Kevin|last5=Chakelian|first5=Anoosh|url=https://www.newstatesman.com/politics/uk/2018/03/meaning-corbynism|title=The meaning of Corbynism|work=New Statesman|date=5 March 2018|accessdate=6 March 2018}}</ref> Murray was appointed as a parliamentary lobby correspondent at the age of 19.<ref name=\"Cohen1\">{{cite news|last=Cohen|first=Nick|url=http://www.newstatesman.com/node/194694|title=Strange bedfellows|work=New Statesman|date=7 April 2003|accessdate=14 December 2015}}</ref> In this post, he \"[marched] with a million Leningraders to mark the 60th anniversary of the October Revolution in 1977\"<ref name=\"Kennedy2019\" /> and was reportedly the first journalist at the scene when [[Airey Neave]] was [[Assassination of Airey Neave|assassinated in 1979]] by the [[Irish National Liberation Army]].<ref name=\"EatonWilbyBushMaguireChakelian\"/> From 1986 to 1987, he worked for the Soviet [[RIA Novosti|Novosti]] news agency.<ref name=\"Cohen1\"/> He was also a ''[[Morning Star (British newspaper)|Morning Star]]'' journalist, a publication to which he still contributes.\n\n===Trade union roles===\nAt the [[Transport and General Workers Union]], an organisation for which Murray worked from 1987 to 1998 and again from 2003,<ref>{{cite news|last=Williams|first=Tom |url=http://www.printweek.com/news/194414//|title=Former ASLEF media boss takes on T&G comms role|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110715115951/http://www.printweek.com/news/194414/|work=PR Week UK|date=7 November 2003|archive-date=15 July 2011}}</ref> he was heavily involved in the conduct of the [[British Airways]] cabin crew strike of 1997, and in the successful general secretary election campaigns of [[Bill Morris, Baron Morris of Handsworth|Bill Morris]] (1991 and 1995) and [[Tony Woodley]] (2003) and, after the formation of Unite as a merger of the T&G and Amicus, of [[Len McCluskey]] in 2010. \nMurray was appointed as chief of staff for [[Unite the Union|Unite]] in 2011 following Len McCluskey's election as general secretary late the previous year.<ref name=\"Wilby\"/> Responsible for most of the union's central departments and for its ten regions, he was elected to the [[TUC General Council]] in April 2011. Ahead of the public sector pension strike, he was named by Education Secretary [[Michael Gove]] in November 2011 as being, along with McCluskey and [[Mark Serwotka]], one of three union \"militants\" who were \"itching for a fight\".\n\nHe has also worked as an official for the [[Associated Society of Locomotive Engineers and Firemen]] (ASLEF).\n\nMurray defended [[Arthur Scargill]] in a review of ''Marching to the Fault Line'' by [[Francis Beckett]] and [[David Hencke]], which criticises the [[National Union of Mineworkers (Great Britain)|NUM]] leader's role in the [[UK miners' strike (1984\u20131985)|miners' strike]], advising ''[[Morning Star (UK newspaper)|Morning Star]]'' readers not to buy the book as doing so would only \"feed the jackals\".<ref>{{cite news|last=Murray|first=Andrew|url=http://www.morningstaronline.co.uk/index.php/news/content/view/full/72972|title=Miners strike hatchet job|work=Morning Star|date=13 March 2009|access-date=30 July 2010|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120511023918/http://www.morningstaronline.co.uk/index.php/news/content/view/full/72972|archive-date=11 May 2012|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n===Politicial activity===\nMurray joined the Communist Party of Great Britain in 1976, aged 18, and became associated with its [[Straight Left]] faction. At this time, Murray became a close friend of [[Seumas Milne]], who was also active in Straight Left.<ref name=\"EatonWilbyBushMaguireChakelian\"/><ref name=\"Wilby\">{{cite news|last=Wilby|first=Peter|url=https://www.newstatesman.com/politics/uk/2016/04/thin-controller|title=The Thin Controller|work=New Statesman|date=16 April 2016}}</ref> Murray's allies during the period have been described by [[Francis Beckett]] as \"more extreme than most of the Stalinists I knew. The Stalinists were known as [[tankies]], but Murray\u2019s lot were super-tankies\".<ref name=\"Wilby\"/> Following the dissolution of the CPGB in 1991 he was a leader of the Communist Liaison group, which itself dissolved in 1995 with Murray and its other members joining the [[Communist Party of Britain]].<ref name=\"Harris\">{{cite news|last=Harris|first=John|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/dec/11/stop-the-war-chair-andrew-murray-interview-jeremy-corbyn|title=Stop the War chair Andrew Murray: \u2018Everyone sees friends at Christmas. But Jeremy, apparently, has a problem\u2019|work=The Guardian|date=11 December 2015|accessdate=11 December 2015}}</ref> Murray served on the Communist Party of Britain's executive committee from 2000 to 2004, and was an advocate of the party supporting the [[Respect Coalition]] in the [[2004 European Parliament election in the United Kingdom|European]] and [[2004 United Kingdom local elections|municipal elections]] that year. He served once more on the party's executive from 2008 until 2011. He told [[John Harris (critic)|John Harris]] in 2015: \"Communism still represents, in my view, a society worth working towards \u2013 albeit not by the methods of the 20th century, which failed\".<ref name=\"Harris\"/>\n\nAs [[Chairman|chair]] of [[Stop the War Coalition|Stop the War]], Murray presided at the concluding rally against the [[Iraq War]] in 2003, a rally which is claimed as the largest political demonstration in British history. He announced his intention to stand down as Stop the War chair in June 2011 and was succeeded by the [[Labour Party (UK)|Labour]] MP [[Jeremy Corbyn]] in September 2011. Murray was elected by the Coalition's Steering Committee to the new post of Deputy President, but returned to the position of chair in September 2015, following Corbyn's election as Leader of the Labour Party.\n\n===Labour Party roles===\nBy November 2016, Murray had joined the Labour Party<ref name=\"Maguire\"/><ref name=\"Boffey\"/> and, in May 2017 he was seconded from Unite to Labour headquarters during the [[2017 United Kingdom general election|2017 general election]].<ref name=\"Waugh15May\">{{cite news|last=Waugh|first=Paul|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/entry/jeremy-corbyn-drafts-in-andrew-murray-to-head-2017-general-election-campaign-team-unite-stop-the-war-chair_uk_5918c0ade4b0031e737e7b6d|title=Jeremy Corbyn Drafts In Unite Union Official Andrew Murray To 'Head Up' His Election Campaign Team|work=The Huffington Post|date=14 May 2017|accessdate=15 May 2017}}</ref> The appointment was contentious because of Murray's previous leadership role within the Communist Party of Britain, and was described by one Labour Party source to ''[[HuffPost|The Huffington Post]]'' as \"Corbyn's Labour has gone full Trump. Andrew Murray is the hard-left's [[Steve Bannon]]\".<ref name=\"Sugarman\">{{cite news|last=Sugarman|first=Daniel|url=https://www.thejc.com/news/uk-news/corbyn-appoints-anti-israel-activist-andrew-murray-as-campaign-chief-1.438501|title=Corbyn appoints anti-Israel activist as campaign chief|work=The Jewish Chronicle|date=15 May 2017|accessdate=18 December 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Waugh|first=Paul|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/entry/jeremy-corbyn-defends-andrew-murray-ex-communist-after-drafted-in-as-election-adviser-secondment-unite_uk_5919d8a4e4b07d5f6ba4bf4a|title=Jeremy Corbyn Defends Labour Campaign Role For Ex-Communist Andrew Murray|work=The Huffington Post|date=15 May 2017}}</ref> Asked by journalists about the appointment, Corbyn said Murray \"is a person of enormous abilities and professionalism\" who possesses \"special skills\".<ref>{{cite news|last1=Pidd|first1=Helen|last2=Mills|first2=Sian|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2017/may/15/jeremy-corbyn-labour-nurses-pay-cap-nhs-rcn|title=Jeremy Corbyn vows to help underpaid and overworked nurses|work=The Guardian|date=15 May 2017|accessdate=15 May 2017}}</ref> Shadow Chancellor [[John McDonnell]] defended the decision saying \"He has left the Communist Party, and joined Labour. We are converting people to [[democratic socialism]].\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.politico.eu/article/uk-shadow-chancellor-labour-welcomes-former-communist-as-corbyn-comms-chief/|title=UK shadow chancellor: Labour welcomes former communist as Corbyn comms chief|first=Cynthia|last=Kroet|date=16 May 2017|website=POLITICO}}</ref> The ''[[Daily Mirror]]''{{'}}s Associate Editor [[Kevin Maguire (journalist)|Kevin Maguire]] described him as \"smart, shrewd, pragmatic and witty\".<ref>{{cite news|last1=Maguire|first1=Kevin|title=Commons Confidential: Murray comes in from the cold|url=http://www.newstatesman.com/politics/uk/2016/11/commons-confidential-murray-comes-cold|work=New Statesman|date=25 November 2016|accessdate=15 May 2017}}</ref>\n\nMurray was quoted in ''[[The Guardian]]'' on the day after the election about the unexpected [[exit poll]] announced just after the polling stations had closed. \"There was a tremendous moment of elation when the exit poll was announced because it became apparent that the campaign had achieved the most stunning turnaround in public opinion in seven weeks\" which saw Labour rise \"from mid 20s in the polls at the start of the campaign to denying the Tories a majority. It was a moment of shared achievement\".<ref>{{cite news|last=MacAskill|first=Ewen|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2017/jun/09/corbyn-team-at-labour-hq-stunned-by-exit-polls-on-election-night|title=Corbyn team at Labour HQ 'stunned' by exit polls on election night|work=The Guardian|date=9 June 2017|accessdate=9 June 2017}}</ref> In a December 2017 interview with the ''[[Morning Star (British newspaper)|Morning Star]]'', Murray called for the readmission of [[George Galloway]] to the Labour Party.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://jewishnews.timesofisrael.com/union-chief-calls-for-george-galloways-readmission-to-the-labour-party/|title=Union chief calls for George Galloway\u2019s readmission to the Labour Party|work=Jewish News|date=6 December 2017|accessdate=16 December 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn late February 2018, ''The Guardian'' reported that Murray was working 1\u00bd days a week as a consultant to the Labour Party.<ref>{{cite news|last=Stewart|first=Heather|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2018/feb/26/jeremy-corbyn-makes-unites-andrew-murray-part-time-consultant|title=Jeremy Corbyn makes Unite's Andrew Murray a part-time consultant|work=The Guardian|date=26 February 2018|accessdate=26 February 2018}}</ref>\n\n[[Angela Smith (Sheffield MP)|Angela Smith]] and [[Mike Gapes]], former Labour MPs who left to found the centrist [[The Independent Group|Independent Group]] of MPs, said that Murray's involvement in the Labour Party were factors in their leaving.<ref name=\"Kennedy2019\" /> \n\nMurray is currently a contributor to the ''[[Morning Star (British newspaper)|Morning Star]]'' and ''[[Tribune (magazine)|Tribune]]''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://tribunemag.co.uk/author/andrew-murray|title=Andrew Murray|website=tribunemag.co.uk|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-12}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://morningstaronline.co.uk/author/andrew-murray|title=Andrew Murray|website=Morning Star|language=en|access-date=2020-02-12}}</ref>\n\nIn late February 2020, The ''Financial Times'' reported that Murray had resigned from his role as an adviser to the Labour Party and returned to his role within Unite on a full time basis.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Payne |first1=Sebastian |last2=Pickard |first2=Jim |title=Andrew Murray quits as adviser to Jeremy Corbyn |url=https://www.ft.com/content/dc552842-5289-11ea-8841-482eed0038b1 |accessdate=19 February 2020 |work=Financial Times}}</ref>\n\n==Positions and other work==\n===Admiral Duncan pub bombing===\nRegarding the neo-Nazi [[1999 London nail bombings#Admiral Duncan bomb|Admiral Duncan pub bombing]] in 1999 by [[David Copeland]], Murray wrote in the ''Morning Star'': \"Everything about this episode strikes me as odd. It happened during a war [i.e. the [[NATO bombing of Yugoslavia]]] that is not going particularly well\", and alleged that some neo-Nazi groups \"may very well have been established with MI5 or Special Branch connivance. And certainly the state \u2014 or groups within the security apparatus \u2014 is more than capable of manipulating deranged human-haters without the latter even noticing that they are being manipulated.\"<ref name=\"Kennedy2019\" /> Murray told ''The Times'' in 2019: \"As I wrote at the time my speculations were no more than 'conjecture and supposition'. There is no basis for any suggestion that the bombing of the Admiral Duncan was the responsibility of anyone other than David Copeland.\"<ref name=\"Kennedy2019\" />\n\n===Communism and other issues===\nMurray is considered an apologist for [[Joseph Stalin]] by his critics, such as [[Nick Cohen]]<ref name=\"Cohen1\"/> and [[Tom Watson (Labour politician)|Tom Watson]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2019/dec/28/tom-watson-was-i-disloyal-i-dont-take-kindly-to-being-told-what-to-do|title=Tom Watson: \u2018Was I disloyal? I don't take kindly to being told what to do'|last=|first=|date=28 December 2019|work=The Guardian|access-date=28 December 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nDescribed as an \"admirer\" in ''The Independent on Sunday'' in 2003,<ref name=\"mcsmithcarrell\">Andy McSmith and Severin Carrell [https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/home-news/stalin-apologists-drink-to-the-memory-of-uncle-joe-120991.html \"Stalin apologists drink to the memory of Uncle Joe\",] ''The Independent on Sunday'', 2 March 2003</ref> in 1999 he wrote in his ''Morning Star'' column:\n{{quote|Next Tuesday is the 120th anniversary of the birth of Josef Stalin. His career is the subject of a vast and ever expanding literature. Read it all and, at the end, you are still left paying your money and taking your choice. A socialist system embracing a third of the world and the defeat of Nazi Germany on the one hand. On the other, all accompanied by harsh measures imposed by a one-party regime. Nevertheless, if you believe that the worst crimes visited on humanity this century, from colonialism to Hiroshima and from concentration camps to mass poverty and unemployment have been caused by imperialism, then [Stalin's birthday] might at least be a moment to ponder why the authors of those crimes and their hack propagandists abominate the name of Stalin beyond all others. It was, after all, Stalin's best-known critic, Nikita Khrushchev, who remarked in 1956 that 'against imperialists, we are all Stalinists'.<ref>{{cite news|last=Murray|first=Andrew|url=http://socialaffairsunit.org.uk/digipub/index2.php?option=content&do_pdf=1&id=12|title=Eye's Left|work=Morning Star|date=17 December 1999}} Reprinted in Michael Mosbacher \"British Anti-Americanism\", Social Affairs Unit, 2004, p. 6</ref>}}\n\nIn 1999, Murray said of KGB spy [[Melita Norwood]]: \"She herself says that she has no regrets and I do not see why she should. She took advantage of the position that she was in to give her side a bit of help in the international class struggle. The strength of the Soviet Union was a huge factor in favour of world peace, something which has become more obvious in its absence today. Those who contributed, however slightly, to that strength did all of us a service.\"<ref name=\"Kennedy2019\">{{cite news |last1=Kennedy |first1=Dominic |title=The privately educated red in bed with Corbyn |url=https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/the-privately-educated-red-in-bed-with-corbyn-k85mvskpr |accessdate=10 March 2019 |work=The Times |date=9 March 2019 |url-access=subscription }}</ref> When asked about these comments by ''[[The Times]]'' in 2019, he said \"The Cold War is over. I would under no circumstances condone anyone acting as Melita Norwood did today.\"<ref name=\"Kennedy2019\" />\n\nIn 2008, Murray identified \"one of the successes\" of the \"nationalities policy of the Soviet Union\" as being the promotion of \"[[Korenizatsiya|the cultural, linguistic and educational development]] of each ethnic group, no matter how small or how historically marginalised.\"<ref>{{cite news|last=Murray|first=Andrew|url=http://www.morningstaronline.co.uk/news/layout/set/print/layout/set/print/content/view/full/64276|title=Cheney, Bush and the Georgia crisis|work=Morning Star|date=12 August 2008|access-date=23 May 2010|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120511023610/http://www.morningstaronline.co.uk/news/layout/set/print/layout/set/print/content/view/full/64276|archive-date=11 May 2012|url-status=dead}}</ref> This comment was criticised by author [[Edward Lucas (journalist)|Edward Lucas]] in ''[[The Guardian]]'' who accused Murray of ignoring \"the [[Operation Lentil (Caucasus)|Chechens]], [[Deportation of the Crimean Tatars|Crimean Tatars]] and other victims of [[Population transfer in the Soviet Union|Stalin's murderous deportation policies]].\"<ref>{{cite news|last=Lucas|first=Edward|url=https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2008/sep/03/russia?gusrc=rss&feed=networkfront|title=To Russia, with love|work=[[The Guardian]]|date=3 September 2008}}</ref> In a short history of the CPGB, published in 1995, Murray wrote: \"That things happened in the USSR which were inexcusable and which ultimately prejudiced Socialism\u2019s whole prospect is today undeniable. Whether Communists in the capitalist world could or should have done more than they did is much more contentious\".<ref name=\"Kamm\">{{cite news|last=Kamm|first=Oliver|url=http://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/labour-may-have-a-communist-as-its-general-secretary-8vpd5d953|title=Labour may have a communist as its general secretary|work=The Times|date=19 September 2016|accessdate=19 September 2016}} {{subscription required}}</ref> [[Oliver Kamm]], in ''The Times'' commented in 2016: \"In short, Mr Murray believes that British communists in the 1930s were justified in backing the Great Terror, the Moscow Trials and the Ukraine famine. Mr Murray predictably supports the most nightmarish totalitarian state in the modern world\".<ref name=\"Kamm\"/> Murray was a critic of [[David Miliband]] in his role as Foreign Secretary, arguing that his stance on the [[Russo-Georgian War|2008 Georgian crisis]] revealed him as a '[[neoconservative]]' whose approach had 'made it abundantly clear where he stands on the great divide in world politics today. He is for the [[American imperialism|US empire]]'.<ref>{{cite news|last=Murray|first=Andrew|url=https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2008/aug/22/davidmiliband.labourleadership|title=Miliband's true colours|work=The Guardian|date=22 August 2008}}</ref>\n\nIn his 2015 book ''The Empire and Ukraine'', he described \"the Putin regime\" as \"unquestionably capitalist, of a particularly corrupt and oligarchic sort\".<ref name=\"Kennedy2019\" /> Nevertheless, in June 2018 Murray was banned from entering [[Ukraine]] for three years by the country's [[Security Service of Ukraine|Security Service]], which stated that he was \"considered part of Putin\u2019s global propagandist network, selling Russian lies, especially in relation to Crimea and the war in Ukraine\u2019s east.\"<ref>[https://www.kyivpost.com/ukraine-politics/ukraine-declares-uk-labor-party-adviser-persona-non-grata-for-russian-propaganda.html Ukraine declares UK Labour Party adviser persona non grata for \u2018Russian propaganda\u2019] ''[[Kyiv Post]]'', 17 September 2018</ref>\n\nIn 2003, Murray warned the Communist Party's Executive Committee of what he claimed was a \"clear desire of the USA to effect \u2018regime change\u2019\" in [[North Korea]], stating that \"Our Party has already made its basic position of solidarity with Peoples' Korea clear\".<ref>{{cite web|last=Murray|first=Andrew|url=http://www.communist-party.org.uk/articles/2003/march/10-03-03.shtml |title=Communist Party of Britain: Report To the March 2003 Executive Committee Meeting|accessdate=2010-03-07 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20031210230502/http://www.communist-party.org.uk/articles/2003/march/10-03-03.shtml |archive-date=10 December 2003 |df=dmy }} , The document was removed from the website of the Communist Party of Britain.</ref> In response to a ''[[Daily Telegraph]]'' letter from [[Conservative Party (UK)|Conservative]] MP and Defence Spokesman [[Julian Lewis (politician)|Julian Lewis]],<ref name=\"Cohen1\"/><ref>{{cite news|last=Lewis|first=Julian|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/comment/letters/3589356/Anti-war-protests-led-by-Communist.html|title=(Letter:) Anti-war protests led by Communist|work=The Daily Telegraph|date=25 March 2003}} Reproduced on [http://www.julianlewis.net/press_detail.php?id=128 Lewis's website] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090523030355/http://www.julianlewis.net/press_detail.php?id=128 |date=23 May 2009 }}</ref> he replied that he had made no secret of his political beliefs.<ref>{{cite news|last=Murray|first=Andrew|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/comment/letters/3589391/Stop-the-War-spans-the-spectrum.html|title=(Letter:) Stop the War spans the spectrum|work=The Daily Telegraph|date=26 March 2003}}</ref> \"People throw the word 'Stalinist' around and demean it by trivialising it. But in the case of Murray it is just\", wrote Cohen in 2015.<ref>{{cite news|last=Cohen|first=Nick|url=http://blogs.spectator.co.uk/2015/05/labour-must-understand-that-unite-is-its-enemy/|title=Labour must understand that Unite is its enemy|work=The Spectator|date=15 May 2015|accessdate=9 September 2016}}</ref>\n\nMurray is a vocal critic of Israel. He stated in a 2012 speech that \"Palestine stands today undefeated and unbowed despite the bloody aggression by one of the greatest military powers on earth\" and that \"we have a message for the Israeli embassy, the Israeli government ... every time you kill a Palestinian child, you are digging your own graves\".<ref name=\"Sugarman\"/>\n\n===Writings===\nMurray is the author of several books and numerous pamphlets, including ''The Communist Party of Great Britain: A Historical Analysis to 1941'' (1995),<ref name=\"Kamm\"/> ''Flashpoint World War III'' (1997), ''Off the Rails'' (2001), ''A New Labour Nightmare: Return of the Awkward Squad'' (2003), ''Stop the War: The Story of Britain's Biggest Mass Movement'' (with [[Lindsey German]], 2005), and ''The T&G Story'' (2008). In 2019 Verso Boks published his ''The Fall and Rise of the British Left'' reviewing the fortunes of British Socialism from the 1970s up until the 2017 general election.  Murray also contributes occasionally to ''The Guardian'' and ''Morning Star''.\n\n====The Imperial Controversy====\n''The Imperial Controversy'' (2009) was described [[Nathaniel Mehr]] in ''[[Tribune (magazine)|Tribune]]'' magazine as \"an important and timely book\".<ref>{{cite news|last=Mehr|first=Nathaniel|url=http://www.tribunemagazine.co.uk/2010/05/murray-mints-our-imperial-history/|title=Murray mints our imperial history|work=Tribune|date=26 May 2010}}</ref> In 2019, Murray attracted controversy for arguing in the book that [[Nazi Party]] leader [[Adolf Hitler]] is the most hated historical figure because he killed white rather than non-white people. Murray wrote, \"Hitler is uniquely excoriated because his victims were almost all white Europeans, while those of Britain (and other classic colonialisms \u2014 French, Belgian, Dutch, Italian and Wilhelmine German) were Asian, African and Arabs.\"<ref name=\"Kennedy\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/andrew-murray-hitler-is-the-most-hated-because-he-killed-whites-m3lt0qx78|title=Andrew Murray: Hitler 'is the most-hated because he killed whites'|last=Kennedy|first=Dominic|date=2019-03-09|work=The Times|access-date=2019-03-11|issn=0140-0460|url-access=subscription }}</ref> He also wrote elsewhere in the book: \"There is nothing in the imperial record as chilling as the systematic extermination of the great majority of Europe's Jews.\" <ref name=\"Kennedy\" />\n\n==Private life==\nAndrew Murray was married to [[Susan Michie]] from 1981 to 1997 and to Anna Kruthoffer from 2003 to date. He has three children with Michie \u2013 Jessica Katharine Murray, Jack Douglas Murray and Laura Catriona Murray,<ref name=\"ThePeerage\" /> and a stepdaughter, Sally Charlton.{{citation needed|date=September 2018}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Murray, Andrew}}\n[[Category:1958 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Anti-revisionists]]\n[[Category:British anti-war activists]]\n[[Category:British communists]]\n[[Category:British male journalists]]\n[[Category:British trade unionists]]\n[[Category:Communist Party of Britain members]]\n[[Category:Communist Party of Great Britain members]]\n[[Category:Drummond family]]\n[[Category:Hope family]]\n[[Category:Labour Party (UK) officials]]\n[[Category:Members of the General Council of the Trades Union Congress]]\n[[Category:People educated at Worth School]]\n", "text_old": "{{other people||Andrew Murray (disambiguation)}}\n{{EngvarB|date=August 2014}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2014}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| honorific-prefix   = \n| name               = Andrew Murray\n| honorific-suffix   = \n| image              = \n| imagesize          = \n| smallimage         =\n| alt                = \n| caption            = \n| office             = [[Special advisers (UK government)|Special Political Advisor]]<br />for the [[Her Majesty's Most Loyal Opposition (United Kingdom)|Leader of the Opposition]] \n| leader             = [[Jeremy Corbyn]]\n| term_start         = 26 February 2018\n| term_end           = 18 February 2020<ref>{{cite news |last1=Payne |first1=Sebastian |last2=Pickard |first2=Jim |title=Andrew Murray quits as adviser to Jeremy Corbyn |url=https://www.ft.com/content/dc552842-5289-11ea-8841-482eed0038b1 |accessdate=19 February 2020 |work=Financial Times}}</ref>\n| predecessor        = ''Position established''\n| successor          = \n| office1            = Chair of the [[Stop the War Coalition]]\n| deputy1            = [[Chris Nineham]]\n| president2         = [[Tony Benn]]\n| deputy2            = [[Chris Nineham]]\n| term_start2        = 21 September 2001\n| term_end2          = 14 June 2011\n| majority2          = \n| predecessor2       = ''Position established''\n| successor2         = [[Jeremy Corbyn]]\n| office2            =\n| term_start1        = 12 September 2015\n| term_end1          = 12 October 2016\n| majority1          = \n| predecessor1       = [[Jeremy Corbyn]]\n| successor1         = [[Murad Qureshi]]\n| office3            = [[Chief of Staff]] of [[Unite the Union]]\n| 1blankname3        = {{nowrap|General Secretary}}\n| 1namedata3         = [[Len McCluskey]]  \n| term_start3        = 1 January 2011\n| term_end3          = \n| majority3          = \n| predecessor3       =\n| successor3         = \n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|1958|7|3|df=yes}}\n| birth_place        = \n| death_date         =\n| death_place        = \n| restingplace       = \n| restingplacecoordinates = \n| birthname          = Andrew Philip Drummond-Murray\n| citizenship        = \n| nationality        = \n| party              = [[Labour Party (UK)|Labour Party]] (2016\u2013present)\n| otherparty         = [[Communist Party of Great Britain]] (1976\u20131991)<br />[[Communist Party of Britain]] (1995\u20132016)\n| spouse             = [[Susan Michie]] (1981\u20131997)<br />Anna Kruthoffer (2003\u2013present)\n| partner            =\n| relations          = [[Arthur Hope, 2nd Baron Rankeillour]]<br /><small>(maternal grandfather)</small>\n| children           = \n| parents            = [[Peter Drummond-Murray of Mastrick]]<br />Hon. Barbara Mary Hope\n| residence          = \n| education          = [[Worth School]]\n| alma_mater         =\n| occupation         = Trade union official\n| cabinet            = \n| committees         = [[General Council of the Trades Union Congress]] (2011\u2013present)<br />Executive Committee of the Communist Party of Britain (2000\u20132004, 2008\u20132011)\n| portfolio          = \n| religion           = \n| signature          = \n| signature_alt      = \n| website            = \n| footnotes          = \n}}\n\n'''Andrew Philip Drummond-Murray''' (born 3 July 1958),<ref name=\"ThePeerage\">{{cite news|url=http://www.thepeerage.com/p19.htm#i182|title=Person Page - 19|website=The Peerage|date=23 May 2015|accessdate=17 May 2017}}</ref> commonly known as '''Andrew Murray''', is a British trade union and Labour Party official, and activist. Murray was seconded from Unite to Labour headquarters for the [[2017 United Kingdom general election|2017 general election]], subsequently becoming an adviser to [[Jeremy Corbyn]].\n\nBorn into an aristocratic Scottish family, Murray began his career as a journalist and later became a senior official for various trade unions.<ref>https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2018/dec/16/why-are-labour-party-leaders-so-quiet-on-europe---maybe-it-is-the-lure-of-disaster?CMP=share_btn_tw</ref>\n\nAfter forty years in the [[Communist Party of Great Britain]] (CPGB) and then the [[Communist Party of Britain]], he joined the [[Labour Party (UK)|Labour Party]] towards the end of 2016.<ref name=\"Maguire\">{{cite news|last=Maguire|first=Kevin|url=http://www.newstatesman.com/politics/uk/2016/11/commons-confidential-murray-comes-cold|title=Commons Confidential: Murray comes in from the cold|work=New Statesman|date=25 November 2016|accessdate=15 May 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"Boffey\">{{cite news|last=Boffey|first=Daniel|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2016/dec/10/unite-leaders-aide-andrew-murray-leaves-communist-party-to-join-labour|title=Unite leader's aide leaves Communist party to join Labour|work=The Observer|date=10 December 2016|accessdate=10 December 2016}}</ref> He was chair of the [[Stop the War Coalition]] from its formation in 2001 until June 2011, and again from September 2015 to 2016.\n\nHe is a contributor to the ''[[Morning Star (British newspaper)|Morning Star]]'' and ''[[Tribune (magazine)|Tribune]]''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://tribunemag.co.uk/author/andrew-murray|title=Andrew Murray|website=tribunemag.co.uk|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-12}}</ref><!-- Murray is certainly no longer chair, and Murad Qureshi appears to have replaced him, but sources are vague. -->\n\n==Biography==\n===Education and journalism===\n[[File:Main building at Worth School.jpg|thumb|left|200px|Worth School]]\nMurray was born in 1958 to [[Peter Drummond-Murray of Mastrick]], a [[stockbroker]] and banker who was [[Slains Pursuivant]] from 1981 to 2009, and [[The Honourable]] Barbara Mary Hope, daughter of former Conservative MP and governor of the [[Madras Presidency]] in [[British India]] from 1940 to 1946 [[Arthur Hope, 2nd Baron Rankeillour|Lord Rankeillour]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/peter-drummond-murray-8crb3gxln9k|title=Peter Drummond Murray|work=The Times|location=London|date=13 May 2014|accessdate=17 May 2017}} {{subscription required}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thepeerage.com/p5711.htm#i57103|title=Person Page - 5711: William Edward Peter Louis Drummond-Murray|website=The Peerage|agency=Burke's Peerage|date=14 May 2017|accessdate=17 May 2017}}</ref> He was  educated at [[Worth School]], a Benedictine independent boarding school in Sussex.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thepeerage.com/p19.htm#i182|title=Person Page - 19: Andrew Philip Drummond-Murray|website=The Peerage|agency=Burke's Peerage|date=23 May 2015|accessdate=17 May 2017}}</ref> Murray left school at 16 with 4 [[GCE Ordinary Level (United Kingdom)|'O' levels]].\n\nAfter working as a messenger at ''[[Reader's Digest]]'' and a copy boy for the ''[[The New York Times International Edition|International Herald Tribune]]'', he undertook journalism training at the ''Sussex Express''.<ref name=\"EatonWilbyBushMaguireChakelian\">{{cite news|last1=Eaton|first1=George|last2=Wilby|first2=Peter|last3=Bush|first3=Stephen|last4=Maguire|first4=Kevin|last5=Chakelian|first5=Anoosh|url=https://www.newstatesman.com/politics/uk/2018/03/meaning-corbynism|title=The meaning of Corbynism|work=New Statesman|date=5 March 2018|accessdate=6 March 2018}}</ref> Murray was appointed as a parliamentary lobby correspondent at the age of 19.<ref name=\"Cohen1\">{{cite news|last=Cohen|first=Nick|url=http://www.newstatesman.com/node/194694|title=Strange bedfellows|work=New Statesman|date=7 April 2003|accessdate=14 December 2015}}</ref> In this post, he \"[marched] with a million Leningraders to mark the 60th anniversary of the October Revolution in 1977\"<ref name=\"Kennedy2019\" /> and was reportedly the first journalist at the scene when [[Airey Neave]] was [[Assassination of Airey Neave|assassinated in 1979]] by the [[Irish National Liberation Army]].<ref name=\"EatonWilbyBushMaguireChakelian\"/> From 1986 to 1987, he worked for the Soviet [[RIA Novosti|Novosti]] news agency.<ref name=\"Cohen1\"/> He was also a ''[[Morning Star (British newspaper)|Morning Star]]'' journalist, a publication to which he still contributes.\n\n===Trade union roles===\nAt the [[Transport and General Workers Union]], an organisation for which Murray worked from 1987 to 1998 and again from 2003,<ref>{{cite news|last=Williams|first=Tom |url=http://www.printweek.com/news/194414//|title=Former ASLEF media boss takes on T&G comms role|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110715115951/http://www.printweek.com/news/194414/|work=PR Week UK|date=7 November 2003|archive-date=15 July 2011}}</ref> he was heavily involved in the conduct of the [[British Airways]] cabin crew strike of 1997, and in the successful general secretary election campaigns of [[Bill Morris, Baron Morris of Handsworth|Bill Morris]] (1991 and 1995) and [[Tony Woodley]] (2003) and, after the formation of Unite as a merger of the T&G and Amicus, of [[Len McCluskey]] in 2010. \nMurray was appointed as chief of staff for [[Unite the Union|Unite]] in 2011 following Len McCluskey's election as general secretary late the previous year.<ref name=\"Wilby\"/> Responsible for most of the union's central departments and for its ten regions, he was elected to the [[TUC General Council]] in April 2011. Ahead of the public sector pension strike, he was named by Education Secretary [[Michael Gove]] in November 2011 as being, along with McCluskey and [[Mark Serwotka]], one of three union \"militants\" who were \"itching for a fight\".\n\nHe has also worked as an official for the [[Associated Society of Locomotive Engineers and Firemen]] (ASLEF).\n\nMurray defended [[Arthur Scargill]] in a review of ''Marching to the Fault Line'' by [[Francis Beckett]] and [[David Hencke]], which criticises the [[National Union of Mineworkers (Great Britain)|NUM]] leader's role in the [[UK miners' strike (1984\u20131985)|miners' strike]], advising ''[[Morning Star (UK newspaper)|Morning Star]]'' readers not to buy the book as doing so would only \"feed the jackals\".<ref>{{cite news|last=Murray|first=Andrew|url=http://www.morningstaronline.co.uk/index.php/news/content/view/full/72972|title=Miners strike hatchet job|work=Morning Star|date=13 March 2009|access-date=30 July 2010|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120511023918/http://www.morningstaronline.co.uk/index.php/news/content/view/full/72972|archive-date=11 May 2012|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n===Politicial activity===\nMurray joined the Communist Party of Great Britain in 1976, aged 18, and became associated with its [[Straight Left]] faction. At this time, Murray became a close friend of [[Seumas Milne]], who was also active in Straight Left.<ref name=\"EatonWilbyBushMaguireChakelian\"/><ref name=\"Wilby\">{{cite news|last=Wilby|first=Peter|url=https://www.newstatesman.com/politics/uk/2016/04/thin-controller|title=The Thin Controller|work=New Statesman|date=16 April 2016}}</ref> Murray's allies during the period have been described by [[Francis Beckett]] as \"more extreme than most of the Stalinists I knew. The Stalinists were known as [[tankies]], but Murray\u2019s lot were super-tankies\".<ref name=\"Wilby\"/> Following the dissolution of the CPGB in 1991 he was a leader of the Communist Liaison group, which itself dissolved in 1995 with Murray and its other members joining the [[Communist Party of Britain]].<ref name=\"Harris\">{{cite news|last=Harris|first=John|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/dec/11/stop-the-war-chair-andrew-murray-interview-jeremy-corbyn|title=Stop the War chair Andrew Murray: \u2018Everyone sees friends at Christmas. But Jeremy, apparently, has a problem\u2019|work=The Guardian|date=11 December 2015|accessdate=11 December 2015}}</ref> Murray served on the Communist Party of Britain's executive committee from 2000 to 2004, and was an advocate of the party supporting the [[Respect Coalition]] in the [[2004 European Parliament election in the United Kingdom|European]] and [[2004 United Kingdom local elections|municipal elections]] that year. He served once more on the party's executive from 2008 until 2011. He told [[John Harris (critic)|John Harris]] in 2015: \"Communism still represents, in my view, a society worth working towards \u2013 albeit not by the methods of the 20th century, which failed\".<ref name=\"Harris\"/>\n\nAs [[Chairman|chair]] of [[Stop the War Coalition|Stop the War]], Murray presided at the concluding rally against the [[Iraq War]] in 2003, a rally which is claimed as the largest political demonstration in British history. He announced his intention to stand down as Stop the War chair in June 2011 and was succeeded by the [[Labour Party (UK)|Labour]] MP [[Jeremy Corbyn]] in September 2011. Murray was elected by the Coalition's Steering Committee to the new post of Deputy President, but returned to the position of chair in September 2015, following Corbyn's election as Leader of the Labour Party.\n\n===Labour Party roles===\nBy November 2016, Murray had joined the Labour Party<ref name=\"Maguire\"/><ref name=\"Boffey\"/> and, in May 2017 he was seconded from Unite to Labour headquarters during the [[2017 United Kingdom general election|2017 general election]].<ref name=\"Waugh15May\">{{cite news|last=Waugh|first=Paul|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/entry/jeremy-corbyn-drafts-in-andrew-murray-to-head-2017-general-election-campaign-team-unite-stop-the-war-chair_uk_5918c0ade4b0031e737e7b6d|title=Jeremy Corbyn Drafts In Unite Union Official Andrew Murray To 'Head Up' His Election Campaign Team|work=The Huffington Post|date=14 May 2017|accessdate=15 May 2017}}</ref> The appointment was contentious because of Murray's previous leadership role within the Communist Party of Britain, and was described by one Labour Party source to ''[[HuffPost|The Huffington Post]]'' as \"Corbyn's Labour has gone full Trump. Andrew Murray is the hard-left's [[Steve Bannon]]\".<ref name=\"Sugarman\">{{cite news|last=Sugarman|first=Daniel|url=https://www.thejc.com/news/uk-news/corbyn-appoints-anti-israel-activist-andrew-murray-as-campaign-chief-1.438501|title=Corbyn appoints anti-Israel activist as campaign chief|work=The Jewish Chronicle|date=15 May 2017|accessdate=18 December 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Waugh|first=Paul|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/entry/jeremy-corbyn-defends-andrew-murray-ex-communist-after-drafted-in-as-election-adviser-secondment-unite_uk_5919d8a4e4b07d5f6ba4bf4a|title=Jeremy Corbyn Defends Labour Campaign Role For Ex-Communist Andrew Murray|work=The Huffington Post|date=15 May 2017}}</ref> Asked by journalists about the appointment, Corbyn said Murray \"is a person of enormous abilities and professionalism\" who possesses \"special skills\".<ref>{{cite news|last1=Pidd|first1=Helen|last2=Mills|first2=Sian|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2017/may/15/jeremy-corbyn-labour-nurses-pay-cap-nhs-rcn|title=Jeremy Corbyn vows to help underpaid and overworked nurses|work=The Guardian|date=15 May 2017|accessdate=15 May 2017}}</ref> Shadow Chancellor [[John McDonnell]] defended the decision saying \"He has left the Communist Party, and joined Labour. We are converting people to [[democratic socialism]].\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.politico.eu/article/uk-shadow-chancellor-labour-welcomes-former-communist-as-corbyn-comms-chief/|title=UK shadow chancellor: Labour welcomes former communist as Corbyn comms chief|first=Cynthia|last=Kroet|date=16 May 2017|website=POLITICO}}</ref> The ''[[Daily Mirror]]''{{'}}s Associate Editor [[Kevin Maguire (journalist)|Kevin Maguire]] described him as \"smart, shrewd, pragmatic and witty\".<ref>{{cite news|last1=Maguire|first1=Kevin|title=Commons Confidential: Murray comes in from the cold|url=http://www.newstatesman.com/politics/uk/2016/11/commons-confidential-murray-comes-cold|work=New Statesman|date=25 November 2016|accessdate=15 May 2017}}</ref>\n\nMurray was quoted in ''[[The Guardian]]'' on the day after the election about the unexpected [[exit poll]] announced just after the polling stations had closed. \"There was a tremendous moment of elation when the exit poll was announced because it became apparent that the campaign had achieved the most stunning turnaround in public opinion in seven weeks\" which saw Labour rise \"from mid 20s in the polls at the start of the campaign to denying the Tories a majority. It was a moment of shared achievement\".<ref>{{cite news|last=MacAskill|first=Ewen|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2017/jun/09/corbyn-team-at-labour-hq-stunned-by-exit-polls-on-election-night|title=Corbyn team at Labour HQ 'stunned' by exit polls on election night|work=The Guardian|date=9 June 2017|accessdate=9 June 2017}}</ref> In a December 2017 interview with the ''[[Morning Star (British newspaper)|Morning Star]]'', Murray called for the readmission of [[George Galloway]] to the Labour Party.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://jewishnews.timesofisrael.com/union-chief-calls-for-george-galloways-readmission-to-the-labour-party/|title=Union chief calls for George Galloway\u2019s readmission to the Labour Party|work=Jewish News|date=6 December 2017|accessdate=16 December 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn late February 2018, ''The Guardian'' reported that Murray was working 1\u00bd days a week as a consultant to the Labour Party.<ref>{{cite news|last=Stewart|first=Heather|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2018/feb/26/jeremy-corbyn-makes-unites-andrew-murray-part-time-consultant|title=Jeremy Corbyn makes Unite's Andrew Murray a part-time consultant|work=The Guardian|date=26 February 2018|accessdate=26 February 2018}}</ref>\n\n[[Angela Smith (Sheffield MP)|Angela Smith]] and [[Mike Gapes]], former Labour MPs who left to found the centrist [[The Independent Group|Independent Group]] of MPs, said that Murray's involvement in the Labour Party were factors in their leaving.<ref name=\"Kennedy2019\" /> \n\nMurray is currently a contributor to the ''[[Morning Star (British newspaper)|Morning Star]]'' and ''[[Tribune (magazine)|Tribune]]''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://tribunemag.co.uk/author/andrew-murray|title=Andrew Murray|website=tribunemag.co.uk|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-12}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://morningstaronline.co.uk/author/andrew-murray|title=Andrew Murray|website=Morning Star|language=en|access-date=2020-02-12}}</ref>\n\nIn late February 2020, The ''Financial Times'' reported that Murray had resigned from his role as an adviser to the Labour Party and returned to his role within Unite on a full time basis.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Payne |first1=Sebastian |last2=Pickard |first2=Jim |title=Andrew Murray quits as adviser to Jeremy Corbyn |url=https://www.ft.com/content/dc552842-5289-11ea-8841-482eed0038b1 |accessdate=19 February 2020 |work=Financial Times}}</ref>\n\n==Positions and other work==\n===Admiral Duncan pub bombing===\nRegarding the neo-Nazi [[1999 London nail bombings#Admiral Duncan bomb|Admiral Duncan pub bombing]] in 1999 by [[David Copeland]], Murray wrote in the ''Morning Star'': \"Everything about this episode strikes me as odd. It happened during a war [i.e. the [[NATO bombing of Yugoslavia]]] that is not going particularly well\", and alleged that some neo-Nazi groups \"may very well have been established with MI5 or Special Branch connivance. And certainly the state \u2014 or groups within the security apparatus \u2014 is more than capable of manipulating deranged human-haters without the latter even noticing that they are being manipulated.\"<ref name=\"Kennedy2019\" /> Murray told ''The Times'' in 2019: \"As I wrote at the time my speculations were no more than 'conjecture and supposition'. There is no basis for any suggestion that the bombing of the Admiral Duncan was the responsibility of anyone other than David Copeland.\"<ref name=\"Kennedy2019\" />\n\n===Communism and other issues===\nMurray is considered an apologist for [[Joseph Stalin]] by his critics, such as [[Nick Cohen]].<ref name=\"Cohen1\"/> and [[Tom Watson (Labour politician)|Tom Watson]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2019/dec/28/tom-watson-was-i-disloyal-i-dont-take-kindly-to-being-told-what-to-do|title=Tom Watson: \u2018Was I disloyal? I don't take kindly to being told what to do'|last=|first=|date=28 December 2019|work=The Guardian|access-date=28 December 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nDescribed as an \"admirer\" in ''The Independent on Sunday'' in 2003,<ref name=\"mcsmithcarrell\">Andy McSmith and Severin Carrell [https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/home-news/stalin-apologists-drink-to-the-memory-of-uncle-joe-120991.html \"Stalin apologists drink to the memory of Uncle Joe\",] ''The Independent on Sunday'', 2 March 2003</ref> in 1999 he wrote in his ''Morning Star'' column:\n{{quote|Next Tuesday is the 120th anniversary of the birth of Josef Stalin. His career is the subject of a vast and ever expanding literature. Read it all and, at the end, you are still left paying your money and taking your choice. A socialist system embracing a third of the world and the defeat of Nazi Germany on the one hand. On the other, all accompanied by harsh measures imposed by a one-party regime. Nevertheless, if you believe that the worst crimes visited on humanity this century, from colonialism to Hiroshima and from concentration camps to mass poverty and unemployment have been caused by imperialism, then [Stalin's birthday] might at least be a moment to ponder why the authors of those crimes and their hack propagandists abominate the name of Stalin beyond all others. It was, after all, Stalin's best-known critic, Nikita Khrushchev, who remarked in 1956 that 'against imperialists, we are all Stalinists'.<ref>{{cite news|last=Murray|first=Andrew|url=http://socialaffairsunit.org.uk/digipub/index2.php?option=content&do_pdf=1&id=12|title=Eye's Left|work=Morning Star|date=17 December 1999}} Reprinted in Michael Mosbacher \"British Anti-Americanism\", Social Affairs Unit, 2004, p. 6</ref>}}\n\nIn 1999, Murray said of KGB spy [[Melita Norwood]]: \"She herself says that she has no regrets and I do not see why she should. She took advantage of the position that she was in to give her side a bit of help in the international class struggle. The strength of the Soviet Union was a huge factor in favour of world peace, something which has become more obvious in its absence today. Those who contributed, however slightly, to that strength did all of us a service.\"<ref name=\"Kennedy2019\">{{cite news |last1=Kennedy |first1=Dominic |title=The privately educated red in bed with Corbyn |url=https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/the-privately-educated-red-in-bed-with-corbyn-k85mvskpr |accessdate=10 March 2019 |work=The Times |date=9 March 2019 |url-access=subscription }}</ref> When asked about these comments by ''[[The Times]]'' in 2019, he said \"The Cold War is over. I would under no circumstances condone anyone acting as Melita Norwood did today.\"<ref name=\"Kennedy2019\" />\n\nIn 2008, Murray identified \"one of the successes\" of the \"nationalities policy of the Soviet Union\" as being the promotion of \"[[Korenizatsiya|the cultural, linguistic and educational development]] of each ethnic group, no matter how small or how historically marginalised.\"<ref>{{cite news|last=Murray|first=Andrew|url=http://www.morningstaronline.co.uk/news/layout/set/print/layout/set/print/content/view/full/64276|title=Cheney, Bush and the Georgia crisis|work=Morning Star|date=12 August 2008|access-date=23 May 2010|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120511023610/http://www.morningstaronline.co.uk/news/layout/set/print/layout/set/print/content/view/full/64276|archive-date=11 May 2012|url-status=dead}}</ref> This comment was criticised by author [[Edward Lucas (journalist)|Edward Lucas]] in ''[[The Guardian]]'' who accused Murray of ignoring \"the [[Operation Lentil (Caucasus)|Chechens]], [[Deportation of the Crimean Tatars|Crimean Tatars]] and other victims of [[Population transfer in the Soviet Union|Stalin's murderous deportation policies]].\"<ref>{{cite news|last=Lucas|first=Edward|url=https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2008/sep/03/russia?gusrc=rss&feed=networkfront|title=To Russia, with love|work=[[The Guardian]]|date=3 September 2008}}</ref> In a short history of the CPGB, published in 1995, Murray wrote: \"That things happened in the USSR which were inexcusable and which ultimately prejudiced Socialism\u2019s whole prospect is today undeniable. Whether Communists in the capitalist world could or should have done more than they did is much more contentious\".<ref name=\"Kamm\">{{cite news|last=Kamm|first=Oliver|url=http://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/labour-may-have-a-communist-as-its-general-secretary-8vpd5d953|title=Labour may have a communist as its general secretary|work=The Times|date=19 September 2016|accessdate=19 September 2016}} {{subscription required}}</ref> [[Oliver Kamm]], in ''The Times'' commented in 2016: \"In short, Mr Murray believes that British communists in the 1930s were justified in backing the Great Terror, the Moscow Trials and the Ukraine famine. Mr Murray predictably supports the most nightmarish totalitarian state in the modern world\".<ref name=\"Kamm\"/> Murray was a critic of [[David Miliband]] in his role as Foreign Secretary, arguing that his stance on the [[Russo-Georgian War|2008 Georgian crisis]] revealed him as a '[[neoconservative]]' whose approach had 'made it abundantly clear where he stands on the great divide in world politics today. He is for the [[American imperialism|US empire]]'.<ref>{{cite news|last=Murray|first=Andrew|url=https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2008/aug/22/davidmiliband.labourleadership|title=Miliband's true colours|work=The Guardian|date=22 August 2008}}</ref>\n\nIn his 2015 book ''The Empire and Ukraine'', he described \"the Putin regime\" as \"unquestionably capitalist, of a particularly corrupt and oligarchic sort\".<ref name=\"Kennedy2019\" /> Nevertheless, in June 2018 Murray was banned from entering [[Ukraine]] for three years by the country's [[Security Service of Ukraine|Security Service]], which stated that he was \"considered part of Putin\u2019s global propagandist network, selling Russian lies, especially in relation to Crimea and the war in Ukraine\u2019s east.\"<ref>[https://www.kyivpost.com/ukraine-politics/ukraine-declares-uk-labor-party-adviser-persona-non-grata-for-russian-propaganda.html Ukraine declares UK Labour Party adviser persona non grata for \u2018Russian propaganda\u2019] ''[[Kyiv Post]]'', 17 September 2018</ref>\n\nIn 2003, Murray warned the Communist Party's Executive Committee of what he claimed was a \"clear desire of the USA to effect \u2018regime change\u2019\" in [[North Korea]], stating that \"Our Party has already made its basic position of solidarity with Peoples' Korea clear\".<ref>{{cite web|last=Murray|first=Andrew|url=http://www.communist-party.org.uk/articles/2003/march/10-03-03.shtml |title=Communist Party of Britain: Report To the March 2003 Executive Committee Meeting|accessdate=2010-03-07 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20031210230502/http://www.communist-party.org.uk/articles/2003/march/10-03-03.shtml |archive-date=10 December 2003 |df=dmy }} , The document was removed from the website of the Communist Party of Britain.</ref> In response to a ''[[Daily Telegraph]]'' letter from [[Conservative Party (UK)|Conservative]] MP and Defence Spokesman [[Julian Lewis (politician)|Julian Lewis]],<ref name=\"Cohen1\"/><ref>{{cite news|last=Lewis|first=Julian|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/comment/letters/3589356/Anti-war-protests-led-by-Communist.html|title=(Letter:) Anti-war protests led by Communist|work=The Daily Telegraph|date=25 March 2003}} Reproduced on [http://www.julianlewis.net/press_detail.php?id=128 Lewis's website] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090523030355/http://www.julianlewis.net/press_detail.php?id=128 |date=23 May 2009 }}</ref> he replied that he had made no secret of his political beliefs.<ref>{{cite news|last=Murray|first=Andrew|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/comment/letters/3589391/Stop-the-War-spans-the-spectrum.html|title=(Letter:) Stop the War spans the spectrum|work=The Daily Telegraph|date=26 March 2003}}</ref> \"People throw the word 'Stalinist' around and demean it by trivialising it. But in the case of Murray it is just\", wrote Cohen in 2015.<ref>{{cite news|last=Cohen|first=Nick|url=http://blogs.spectator.co.uk/2015/05/labour-must-understand-that-unite-is-its-enemy/|title=Labour must understand that Unite is its enemy|work=The Spectator|date=15 May 2015|accessdate=9 September 2016}}</ref>\n\nMurray is a vocal critic of Israel. He stated in a 2012 speech that \"Palestine stands today undefeated and unbowed despite the bloody aggression by one of the greatest military powers on earth\" and that \"we have a message for the Israeli embassy, the Israeli government ... every time you kill a Palestinian child, you are digging your own graves\".<ref name=\"Sugarman\"/>\n\n===Writings===\nMurray is the author of several books and numerous pamphlets, including ''The Communist Party of Great Britain: A Historical Analysis to 1941'' (1995),<ref name=\"Kamm\"/> ''Flashpoint World War III'' (1997), ''Off the Rails'' (2001), ''A New Labour Nightmare: Return of the Awkward Squad'' (2003), ''Stop the War: The Story of Britain's Biggest Mass Movement'' (with [[Lindsey German]], 2005), and ''The T&G Story'' (2008). In 2019 Verso Boks published his ''The Fall and Rise of the British Left'' reviewing the fortunes of British Socialism from the 1970s up until the 2017 general election.  Murray also contributes occasionally to ''The Guardian'' and ''Morning Star''.\n\n====The Imperial Controversy====\n''The Imperial Controversy'' (2009) was described [[Nathaniel Mehr]] in ''[[Tribune (magazine)|Tribune]]'' magazine as \"an important and timely book\".<ref>{{cite news|last=Mehr|first=Nathaniel|url=http://www.tribunemagazine.co.uk/2010/05/murray-mints-our-imperial-history/|title=Murray mints our imperial history|work=Tribune|date=26 May 2010}}</ref> In 2019, Murray attracted controversy for arguing in the book that [[Nazi Party]] leader [[Adolf Hitler]] is the most hated historical figure because he killed white rather than non-white people. Murray wrote, \"Hitler is uniquely excoriated because his victims were almost all white Europeans, while those of Britain (and other classic colonialisms \u2014 French, Belgian, Dutch, Italian and Wilhelmine German) were Asian, African and Arabs.\"<ref name=\"Kennedy\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/andrew-murray-hitler-is-the-most-hated-because-he-killed-whites-m3lt0qx78|title=Andrew Murray: Hitler 'is the most-hated because he killed whites'|last=Kennedy|first=Dominic|date=2019-03-09|work=The Times|access-date=2019-03-11|issn=0140-0460|url-access=subscription }}</ref> He also wrote elsewhere in the book: \"There is nothing in the imperial record as chilling as the systematic extermination of the great majority of Europe's Jews.\" <ref name=\"Kennedy\" />\n\n==Private life==\nAndrew Murray was married to [[Susan Michie]] from 1981 to 1997 and to Anna Kruthoffer from 2003 to date. He has three children with Michie \u2013 Jessica Katharine Murray, Jack Douglas Murray and Laura Catriona Murray,<ref name=\"ThePeerage\" /> and a stepdaughter, Sally Charlton.{{citation needed|date=September 2018}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Murray, Andrew}}\n[[Category:1958 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Anti-revisionists]]\n[[Category:British anti-war activists]]\n[[Category:British communists]]\n[[Category:British male journalists]]\n[[Category:British trade unionists]]\n[[Category:Communist Party of Britain members]]\n[[Category:Communist Party of Great Britain members]]\n[[Category:Drummond family]]\n[[Category:Hope family]]\n[[Category:Labour Party (UK) officials]]\n[[Category:Members of the General Council of the Trades Union Congress]]\n[[Category:People educated at Worth School]]\n", "name_user": "Jontel", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eCommunism and other issues", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Andrew_Murray_(trade_unionist)"}
